\lang1033 In person, Rita Skeeter is much warmer and softer than her famously ferocious quill-portraits might suggest. Greeting me in the hallway of her cozy home, she leads me straight into the kitchen for a cup of tea, a slice of pound cake and, it goes without saying, a steaming vat of freshest gossip.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, of course, Dumbledore is a biographer\rquote s dream,\rdblquote  says Skeeter. \ldblquote Such a long, full life. I\rquote m sure my book will be the first of very, very many.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Skeeter was certainly quick off the mark. Her nine-hundred-page book was completed a mere four weeks after Dumbledore\rquote s mysterious death in June. I ask her how she managed this superfast feat.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, when you\rquote ve been a journalist as long as I have, working to a deadline is second nature. I knew that the Wizarding world was clamoring for the full story and I wanted to be the first to meet that need.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 I mention the recent, widely publicized remarks\lang3081  \lang1033 of Elphias Doge, Special Advisor to the Wizen\-gamot and longstanding friend of Albus Dumble\-dore\rquote s, that \ldblquote Skeeter\rquote s book contains less fact than a Chocolate Frog card.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
