Harry ran back upstairs to his bedroom, arriving at the window just in time to see the Dursleys\rquote  car swinging out of the drive and off up the road. Dedalus\rquote s top hat was visible between Aunt Petunia and Dudley in the backseat. The car turned right at the end of Privet Drive, its windows burned scarlet for a moment in the now setting sun, and then it was gone.\par
Harry picked up Hedwig\rquote s cage, his Firebolt, and his rucksack, gave his unnaturally tidy bedroom one last sweeping look, and then made his ungainly way back downstairs to the hall, where he depos\-ited cage, broomstick, and bag near the foot of the stairs. The light was fading rapidly now, the hall full of shadows in the evening light. It felt most strange to stand here in the silence and know that he was about to leave the house for the last time. Long ago, when he had been left alone while the Dursleys went out to enjoy themselves, the hours of solitude had been a rare treat: Pausing only to sneak something tasty from the fridge, he had rushed upstairs to play on\lang3081  \lang1033 Dudley\rquote s computer, or put on the television and flicked through the channels to his heart\rquote s content. It gave him an odd, empty feeling to remember those times; it was like remembering a younger brother whom he had lost.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t you want to take a last look at the place?\rdblquote  he asked Hed\-wig, who was still sulking with her head under her wing. \ldblquote We\rquote ll never be here again. Don\rquote t you want to remember all the good times? I mean, look at this doormat. What memories \'85 Dudley puked on it after I saved him from the dementors. \'85 Turns out he was grateful after all, can you believe it?\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 And last summer, Dumble\-dore walked through that front door. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry lost the thread of his thoughts for a moment and Hedwig did nothing to help him retrieve it, but continued to sit with her head under her wing. Harry turned his back on the front door.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And under here, Hedwig\rdblquote  \emdash  Harry pulled open a door under the stairs \emdash  \ldblquote is where I used to sleep! You never knew me then \emdash  Blimey, it\rquote s small, I\rquote d forgotten. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry looked around at the stacked shoes and umbrellas, re\-membering how he used to wake every morning looking up at the underside of the staircase, which was more often than not adorned with a spider or two. Those had been the days before he had known anything about his true identity; before he had found out how his parents had died or why such strange things often happened around him. But Harry could still remember the dreams that had dogged him, even in those days: confused dreams involving flashes of green light and once \emdash  Uncle Vernon had nearly crashed the car when Harry had recounted it \emdash  a flying motorbike \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a sudden, deafening roar from somewhere nearby. Harry straightened up with a jerk and smacked the top of his head\lang3081  \lang1033 on the low door frame. Pausing only to employ a few of Uncle Vernon\rquote s choicest swear words, he staggered back into the kitchen, clutching his head and staring out of the window into the back garden.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The darkness seemed to be rippling, the air itself quivering. Then, one by one, figures began to pop into sight as their Disillusionment Charms lifted. Dominating the scene was Hagrid, wearing a helmet and goggles and sitting astride an enormous motorbike with a black sidecar attached. All around him other people were dismounting from brooms and, in two cases, skeletal, black winged horses.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Wrenching open the back door, Harry hurtled into their midst. There was a general cry of greeting as Hermione flung her arms around him, Ron clapped him on the back, and Hagrid said, \ldblquote All righ\rquote , Harry? Ready fer the off?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Definitely,\rdblquote  said Harry, beaming around at them all. \ldblquote But I wasn\rquote t expecting this many of you!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Change of plan,\rdblquote  growled Mad-Eye, who was holding two enor\-mous, bulging sacks, and whose magical eye was spinning from darkening sky to house to garden with dizzying rapidity. \ldblquote Let\rquote s get undercover before we talk you through it.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry led them all back into the kitchen where, laughing and chattering, they settled on chairs, sat themselves upon Aunt Petunia\rquote s gleaming work surfaces, or leaned up against her spotless appliances: Ron, long and lanky; Hermione, her bushy hair tied back in a long plait; Fred and George, grinning identically; Bill, badly scarred and long-haired; Mr. Weasley, kind-faced, balding, his spectacles a little awry; Mad-Eye, battle-worn, one-legged, his bright blue magical eye whizzing in its socket; Tonks, whose short hair was her favorite shade of bright pink; Lupin, grayer, more lined; Fleur, slender and\lang3081  \lang1033 beautiful, with her long silvery blonde hair; Kingsley, bald, black, broad-shouldered; Hagrid, with his wild hair and beard, standing hunchbacked to avoid hitting his head on the ceiling; and Mun\-dungus Fletcher, small, dirty, and hangdog, with his droopy basset hound\rquote s eyes and matted hair. Harry\rquote s heart seemed to expand and glow at the sight: He felt incredibly fond of all of them, even Mund\-ungus, whom he had tried to strangle the last time they had met.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Kingsley, I thought you were looking after the Muggle Prime Minister?\rdblquote  he called across the room.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He can get along without me for one night,\rdblquote  said Kingsley. \ldblquote You\rquote re more important.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry, guess what?\rdblquote  said Tonks from her perch on top of the washing machine, and she wiggled her left hand at him; a ring glit\-tered there.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You got married?\rdblquote  Harry yelped, looking from her to Lupin.\lang3081\par
