\lang1033\ldblquote That\rquote s him, it\rquote s him, it\rquote s the real one!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The hooded Death Eater\rquote s shout reached Harry even above the thunder of the motorbike\rquote s engine: Next moment, both pursuers had fallen back and disappeared from view.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry, what\rquote s happened?\rdblquote  bellowed Hagrid. \ldblquote Where\rquote ve they gone?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t know!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Harry was afraid: The hooded Death Eater had shouted \ldblquote It\rquote s the real one!\rdblquote ; how had he known? He gazed around at the appar\-ently empty darkness and felt its menace. Where were they?\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He clambered around on the seat to face forward and seized hold of the back of Hagrid\rquote s jacket.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hagrid, do the dragon-fire thing again, let\rquote s get out of here!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hold on tight, then, Harry!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a deafening, screeching roar again and the white-blue fire shot from the exhaust: Harry felt himself slipping backward off what little of the seat he had, Hagrid flung backward upon him, barely maintaining his grip on the handlebars \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I think we\rquote ve lost \rquote em Harry, I think we\rquote ve done it!\rdblquote  yelled Hagrid.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Harry was not convinced: Fear lapped at him as he looked left and right for pursuers he was sure would come. \'85 Why had they fallen back? One of them had still had a wand. \'85 \i It\rquote s him\i0  \'85 \i it\rquote s the real one. \'85\i0  They had said it right after he had tried to Disarm Stan. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote re nearly there, Harry, we\rquote ve nearly made it!\rdblquote  shouted Hagrid.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry felt the bike drop a little, though the lights down on the ground still seemed remote as stars.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Then the scar on his forehead burned like fire; as a Death Eater appeared on either side of the bike, two Killing Curses missed Harry by millimeters, cast from behind \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And then Harry saw him. Voldemort was flying like smoke on the wind, without broomstick or thestral to hold him, his snake\-like face gleaming out of the blackness, his white fingers raising his wand again \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hagrid let out a bellow of fear and steered the motorbike into a vertical dive. Clinging on for dear life, Harry sent Stunning Spells flying at random into the whirling night. He saw a body fly past\lang3081  \lang1033 him and knew he had hit one of them, but then he heard a bang and saw sparks from the engine; the motorbike spiraled through the air, completely out of control \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Green jets of light shot past them again. Harry had no idea which way was up, which down: His scar was still burning; he expected to die at any second. A hooded figure on a broomstick was feet from him, he saw it raise its arm \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote NO!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 With a shout of fury Hagrid launched himself off the bike at the Death Eater; to his horror, Harry saw both Hagrid and the Death Eater falling out of sight, their combined weight too much for the broomstick \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Barely gripping the plummeting bike with his knees, Harry heard Voldemort scream, \ldblquote\i Mine\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It was over: He could not see or hear where Voldemort was; he glimpsed another Death Eater swooping out of the way and heard, \ldblquote\i Avada\i0  \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 As the pain from Harry\rquote s scar forced his eyes shut, his wand acted of its own accord. He felt it drag his hand around like some great magnet, saw a spurt of golden fire through his half-closed eyelids, heard a crack and a scream of fury. The remaining Death Eater yelled; Voldemort screamed, \ldblquote\i No\i0 !\rdblquote : Somehow, Harry found his nose an inch from the dragon-fire button. He punched it with his wand-free hand and the bike shot more flames into the air, hurtling straight toward the ground.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hagrid!\rdblquote  Harry called, holding on to the bike for dear life. \ldblquote Hagrid \emdash  \i Accio Hagrid\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The motorbike sped up, sucked toward the earth. Face level with the handlebars, Harry could see nothing but distant lights growing\lang3081  \lang1033 nearer and nearer: He was going to crash and there was nothing he could do about it. Behind him came another scream, \i\ldblquote Your wand, Selwyn, give me your wand\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He felt Voldemort before he saw him. Looking sideways, he stared into the red eyes and was sure they would be the last thing he ever saw: Voldemort preparing to curse him once more \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And then Voldemort vanished. Harry looked down and saw Hagrid spread-eagled on the ground below him. He pulled hard at the handlebars to avoid hitting him, groped for the brake, but with an earsplitting, ground-trembling crash, he smashed into a muddy pond.\lang3081\par
