\lang1033 Harry understood \ldblquote they\rdblquote  to mean Fleur and Mrs. Weasley.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s one extra day,\rdblquote  said Ron, when Harry looked mutinous.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t they realize how important \emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \rquote Course they don\rquote t,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote They haven\rquote t got a clue. And now you mention it, I wanted to talk to you about that.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron glanced toward the door into the hall to check that Mrs. Weasley was not returning yet, then leaned in closer to Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Mum\rquote s been trying to get it out of Hermione and me. What we\rquote re off to do. She\rquote ll try you next, so brace yourself. Dad and Lupin\rquote ve both asked as well, but when we said Dumbledore told you not to tell anyone except us, they dropped it. Not Mum, though. She\rquote s determined.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron\rquote s prediction came true within hours. Shortly before lunch, Mrs. Weasley detached Harry from the others by asking him to help identify a lone man\rquote s sock that she thought might have come out of his rucksack. Once she had him cornered in the tiny scullery off the kitchen, she started.\lang3081\par
