\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, of course not,\rdblquote  said Mrs. Weasley with a sudden and rather unnerving return to her casual tone. \ldblquote I should have realized. Well, Harry, while we\rquote ve still got you here, you won\rquote t mind helping with the preparations for Bill and Fleur\rquote s wedding, will you? There\rquote s still so much to do.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No \emdash  I \emdash  of course not,\rdblquote  said Harry, disconcerted by this sud\-den change of subject.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Sweet of you,\rdblquote  she replied, and she smiled as she left the scullery.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 From that moment on, Mrs. Weasley kept Harry, Ron, and Her\-mione so busy with preparations for the wedding that they hardly had any time to think. The kindest explanation of this behavior would have been that Mrs. Weasley wanted to distract them all from thoughts of Mad-Eye and the terrors of their recent journey. After two days of nonstop cutlery cleaning, of color-matching fa\-vors, ribbons, and flowers, of de-gnoming the garden and helping Mrs. Weasley cook vast batches of canap\'e9s, however, Harry started to suspect her of a different motive. All the jobs she handed out seemed to keep him, Ron, and Hermione away from one another; he had not had a chance to speak to the two of them alone since the first night, when he had told them about Voldemort torturing Ollivander.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I think Mum thinks that if she can stop the three of you getting together and planning, she\rquote ll be able to delay you leaving,\rdblquote  Ginny told Harry in an undertone, as they laid the table for dinner on the third night of his stay.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And then what does she think\rquote s going to happen?\rdblquote  Harry mut\-tered. \ldblquote Someone else might kill off Voldemort while she\rquote s holding us here making vol-au-vents?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He had spoken without thinking, and saw Ginny\rquote s face whiten.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So it\rquote s true?\rdblquote  she said. \ldblquote That\rquote s what you\rquote re trying to do?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I \emdash  not \emdash  I was joking,\rdblquote  said Harry evasively.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They stared at each other, and there was something more than shock in Ginny\rquote s expression. Suddenly Harry became aware that\lang3081  \lang1033 this was the first time that he had been alone with her since those stolen hours in secluded corners of the Hogwarts grounds. He was sure she was remembering them too. Both of them jumped as the door opened, and Mr. Weasley, Kingsley, and Bill walked in.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They were often joined by other Order members for dinner now, because the Burrow had replaced number twelve, Grimmauld Place as the headquarters. Mr. Weasley had explained that after the death of Dumbledore, their Secret-Keeper, each of the people to whom Dumbledore had confided Grimmauld Place\rquote s location had become a Secret-Keeper in turn.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And as there are around twenty of us, that greatly dilutes the power of the Fidelius Charm. Twenty times as many opportunities for the Death Eaters to get the secret out of somebody. We can\rquote t expect it to hold much longer.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But surely Snape will have told the Death Eaters the address by now?\rdblquote  asked Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, Mad-Eye set up a couple of curses against Snape in case he turns up there again. We hope they\rquote ll be strong enough both to keep him out and to bind his tongue if he tries to talk about the place, but we can\rquote t be sure. It would have been insane to keep us\-ing the place as headquarters now that its protection has become so shaky.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The kitchen was so crowded that evening it was difficult to ma\-neuver knives and forks. Harry found himself crammed beside Ginny; the unsaid things that had just passed between them made him wish they had been separated by a few more people. He was trying so hard to avoid brushing her arm he could barely cut his chicken.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No news about Mad-Eye?\rdblquote  Harry asked Bill.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Nothing,\rdblquote  replied Bill.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They had not been able to hold a funeral for Moody, because Bill and Lupin had failed to recover his body. It had been difficult to know where he might have fallen, given the darkness and the confusion of the battle.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The \i Daily Prophet\i0  hasn\rquote t said a word about him dying or about finding the body,\rdblquote  Bill went on. \ldblquote But that doesn\rquote t mean much. It\rquote s keeping a lot quiet these days.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And they still haven\rquote t called a hearing about all the underage magic I used escaping the Death Eaters?\rdblquote  Harry called across the table to Mr. Weasley, who shook his head.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Because they know I had no choice or because they don\rquote t want me to tell the world Voldemort attacked me?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The latter, I think. Scrimgeour doesn\rquote t want to admit that You-Know-Who is as powerful as he is, nor that Azkaban\rquote s seen a mass breakout.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, why tell the public the truth?\rdblquote  said Harry, clenching his knife so tightly that the faint scars on the back of his right hand stood out, white against his skin: \i I must not tell lies.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Isn\rquote t anyone at the Ministry prepared to stand up to him?\rdblquote  asked Ron angrily.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Of course, Ron, but people are terrified,\rdblquote  Mr. Weasley replied, \ldblquote terrified that they will be next to disappear, their children the next to be attacked! There are nasty rumors going around; I for one don\rquote t believe the Muggle Studies professor at Hogwarts resigned. She hasn\rquote t been seen for weeks now. Meanwhile Scrimgeour remains shut up in his office all day: I just hope he\rquote s working on a plan.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a pause in which Mrs. Weasley magicked the empty plates onto the work surface and served apple tart.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We must decide \rquote ow you will be disguised, \rquote Arry,\rdblquote  said Fleur, once everyone had pudding. \ldblquote For ze wedding,\rdblquote  she added, when he looked confused. \ldblquote Of course, none of our guests are Death Eaters, but we cannot guarantee zat zey will not let something slip after zey \rquote ave \rquote ad champagne.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
