\lang1033\ldblquote No, Harry, dear, I\rquote d much rather you helped Arthur muck out the chickens, and Hermione, I\rquote d be ever so grateful if you\rquote d change the sheets for Monsieur and Madame Delacour; you know they\rquote re arriving at eleven tomorrow morning.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But as it turned out, there was very little to do for the chickens.\lang3081  \lang1033\ldblquote There\rquote s no need to, er, mention it to Molly,\rdblquote  Mr. Weasley told Harry, blocking his access to the coop, \ldblquote but, er, Ted Tonks sent me most of what was left of Sirius\rquote s bike and, er, I\rquote m hiding \emdash  that\rquote s to say, keeping \emdash  it in here. Fantastic stuff: There\rquote s an exhaust gas\-kin, as I believe it\rquote s called, the most magnificent battery, and it\rquote ll be a great opportunity to find out how brakes work. I\rquote m going to try and put it all back together again when Molly\rquote s not \emdash  I mean, when I\rquote ve got time.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
