\lang1033\ldblquote It is!\rdblquote  said Ron, clearly frustrated that Harry had not grasped the brilliance of the plan. \ldblquote Look, when we three don\rquote t turn up at\lang3081  \lang1033 Hogwarts again, everyone\rquote s going to think Hermione and I must be with you, right? Which means the Death Eaters will go straight for our families to see if they\rquote ve got information on where you are.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But hopefully it\rquote ll look like I\rquote ve gone away with Mum and Dad; a lot of Muggle-borns are talking about going into hiding at the moment,\rdblquote  said Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We can\rquote t hide my whole family, it\rquote ll look too fishy and they can\rquote t all leave their jobs,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote So we\rquote re going to put out the story that I\rquote m seriously ill with spattergroit, which is why I can\rquote t go back to school. If anyone comes calling to investigate, Mum or Dad can show them the ghoul in my bed, covered in pustules. Spattergroit\rquote s really contagious, so they\rquote re not going to want to go near him. It won\rquote t matter that he can\rquote t say anything, either, because apparently you can\rquote t once the fungus has spread to your uvula.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
