\pard\qc The Wedding\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi284\qj\fs24\par
Three o\rquote clock on the following afternoon found Harry, Ron, Fred, and George standing outside the great white marquee in the orchard, awaiting the arrival of the wedding guests. Harry had taken a large dose of Polyjuice Potion and was now the double of a redheaded Muggle boy from the local village, Ottery St. Catchpole, from whom Fred had stolen hairs using a Summoning Charm. The plan was to introduce Harry as \ldblquote Cousin Barny\rdblquote  and trust to the great number of Weasley relatives to camouflage him.\par
All four of them were clutching seating plans, so that they could help show people to the right seats. A host of white-robed waiters had arrived an hour earlier, along with a golden-jacketed band, and all of these wizards were currently sitting a short distance away un\-der a tree; Harry could see a blue haze of pipe smoke issuing from the spot.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Behind Harry, the entrance to the marquee revealed rows and rows of fragile golden chairs set on either side of a long purple carpet.\lang3081  \lang1033 The supporting poles were entwined with white and gold flowers. Fred and George had fastened an enormous bunch of golden bal\-loons over the exact point where Bill and Fleur would shortly be\-come husband and wife. Outside, butterflies and bees were hovering lazily over the grass and hedgerow. Harry was rather uncomfortable. The Muggle boy whose appearance he was affecting was slightly fat\-ter than him, and his dress robes felt hot and tight in the full glare of a summer\rquote s day.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote When I get married,\rdblquote  said Fred, tugging at the collar of his own robes, \ldblquote I won\rquote t be bothering with any of this nonsense. You can all wear what you like, and I\rquote ll put a full Body-Bind Curse on Mum until it\rquote s all over.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote She wasn\rquote t too bad this morning, considering,\rdblquote  said George. \ldblquote Cried a bit about Percy not being here, but who wants him? Oh blimey, brace yourselves \emdash  here they come, look.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Brightly colored figures were appearing, one by one, out of no\-where at the distant boundary of the yard. Within minutes a proces\-sion had formed, which began to snake its way up through the garden toward the marquee. Exotic flowers and bewitched birds fluttered on the witches\rquote  hats, while precious gems glittered from many of the wizards\rquote  cravats; a hum of excited chatter grew louder and louder, drowning the sound of the bees as the crowd approached the tent.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Excellent, I think I see a few veela cousins,\rdblquote  said George, cran\-ing his neck for a better look. \ldblquote They\rquote ll need help understanding our English customs, I\rquote ll look after them. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
