Everything seemed fuzzy, slow. Harry and Hermione jumped to their feet and drew their wands. Many people were only just realizing that something strange had happened; heads were still turning toward the silver cat as it vanished. Silence spread outward in cold ripples from the place where the Patronus had landed. Then somebody screamed.\par
Harry and Hermione threw themselves into the panicking crowd. Guests were sprinting in all directions; many were Disapparating; the protective enchantments around the Burrow had broken.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ron!\rdblquote  Hermione cried. \ldblquote Ron, where are you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 As they pushed their way across the dance floor, Harry saw cloaked and masked figures appearing in the crowd; then he saw Lupin and Tonks, their wands raised, and heard both of them shout, \ldblquote\i Protego\i0 !\rdblquote , a cry that was echoed on all sides \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ron! Ron!\rdblquote  Hermione called, half sobbing as she and Harry were buffeted by terrified guests: Harry seized her hand to make\lang3081  \lang1033 sure they weren\rquote t separated as a streak of light whizzed over their heads, whether a protective charm or something more sinister he did not know \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And then Ron was there. He caught hold of Hermione\rquote s free arm, and Harry felt her turn on the spot; sight and sound were ex\-tinguished as darkness pressed in upon him; all he could feel was Hermione\rquote s hand as he was squeezed through space and time, away from the Burrow, away from the descending Death Eaters, away, perhaps, from Voldemort himself. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Where are we?\rdblquote  said Ron\rquote s voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry opened his eyes. For a moment he thought they had not left the wedding after all: They still seemed to be surrounded by people.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Tottenham Court Road,\rdblquote  panted Hermione. \ldblquote Walk, just walk, we need to find somewhere for you to change.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry did as she asked. They half walked, half ran up the wide dark street thronged with late-night revelers and lined with closed shops, stars twinkling above them. A double-decker bus rumbled by and a group of merry pub-goers ogled them as they passed; Harry and Ron were still wearing dress robes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hermione, we haven\rquote t got anything to change into,\rdblquote  Ron told her, as a young woman burst into raucous giggles at the sight of him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Why didn\rquote t I make sure I had the Invisibility Cloak with me?\rdblquote  said Harry, inwardly cursing his own stupidity. \ldblquote All last year I kept it on me and \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s okay, I\rquote ve got the Cloak, I\rquote ve got clothes for both of you,\rdblquote  said Hermione. \ldblquote Just try and act naturally until \emdash  this will do.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She led them down a side street, then into the shelter of a shad\-owy alleyway.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote When you say you\rquote ve got the Cloak, and clothes \'85\rdblquote  said Harry, frowning at Hermione, who was carrying nothing except her small beaded handbag, in which she was now rummaging.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes, they\rquote re here,\rdblquote  said Hermione, and to Harry and Ron\rquote s ut\-ter astonishment, she pulled out a pair of jeans, a sweatshirt, some maroon socks, and finally the silvery Invisibility Cloak.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How the ruddy hell \emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Undetectable Extension Charm,\rdblquote  said Hermione. \ldblquote Tricky, but I think I\rquote ve done it okay; anyway, I managed to fit everything we need in here.\rdblquote  She gave the fragile-looking bag a little shake and it echoed like a cargo hold as a number of heavy objects rolled around inside it. \ldblquote Oh, damn, that\rquote ll be the books,\rdblquote  she said, peering into it, \ldblquote and I had them all stacked by subject. \'85 Oh well. \'85 Harry, you\rquote d better take the Invisibility Cloak. Ron, hurry up and change. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote When did you do all this?\rdblquote  Harry asked as Ron stripped off his robes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I told you at the Burrow, I\rquote ve had the essentials packed for days, you know, in case we needed to make a quick getaway. I packed your rucksack this morning, Harry, after you changed, and put it in here. \'85 I just had a feeling. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re amazing, you are,\rdblquote  said Ron, handing her his bundled-up robes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Thank you,\rdblquote  said Hermione, managing a small smile as she pushed the robes into the bag. \ldblquote Please, Harry, get that Cloak on!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry threw the Invisibility Cloak around his shoulders and pulled it up over his head, vanishing from sight. He was only just beginning to appreciate what had happened.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The others \emdash  everyone at the wedding \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We can\rquote t worry about that now,\rdblquote  whispered Hermione. \ldblquote It\rquote s you they\rquote re after, Harry, and we\rquote ll just put everyone in even more danger by going back.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote She\rquote s right,\rdblquote  said Ron, who seemed to know that Harry was about to argue, even if he could not see his face. \ldblquote Most of the Order was there, they\rquote ll look after everyone.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry nodded, then remembered that they could not see him, and said, \ldblquote Yeah.\rdblquote  But he thought of Ginny, and fear bubbled like acid in his stomach.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Come on, I think we ought to keep moving,\rdblquote  said Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They moved back up the side street and onto the main road again, where a group of men on the opposite side was singing and weaving across the pavement.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Just as a matter of interest, why Tottenham Court Road?\rdblquote  Ron asked Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ve no idea, it just popped into my head, but I\rquote m sure we\rquote re safer out in the Muggle world, it\rquote s not where they\rquote ll expect us to be.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote True,\rdblquote  said Ron, looking around, \ldblquote but don\rquote t you feel a bit \emdash  exposed?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Where else is there?\rdblquote  asked Hermione, cringing as the men on the other side of the road started wolf-whistling at her. \ldblquote We can hardly book rooms at the Leaky Cauldron, can we? And Grimmauld Place is out if Snape can get in there. \'85 I suppose we could try my parents\rquote  house, though I think there\rquote s a chance they might check there. \'85 Oh, I wish they\rquote d shut up!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote All right, darling?\rdblquote  the drunkest of the men on the other pave\-ment was yelling. \ldblquote Fancy a drink? Ditch ginger and come and have a pint!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Let\rquote s sit down somewhere,\rdblquote  Hermione said hastily as Ron opened his mouth to shout back across the road. \ldblquote Look, this will do, in here!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It was a small and shabby all-night caf\'e9. A light layer of grease lay on all the Formica-topped tables, but it was at least empty. Harry slipped into a booth first and Ron sat next to him opposite Hermione, who had her back to the entrance and did not like it: She glanced over her shoulder so frequently she appeared to have a twitch. Harry did not like being stationary; walking had given the illusion that they had a goal. Beneath the Cloak he could feel the last vestiges of Polyjuice leaving him, his hands returning to their usual length and shape. He pulled his glasses out of his pocket and put them on again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 After a minute or two, Ron said, \ldblquote You know, we\rquote re not far from the Leaky Cauldron here, it\rquote s only in Charing Cross \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ron, we can\rquote t!\rdblquote  said Hermione at once.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Not to stay there, but to find out what\rquote s going on!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We know what\rquote s going on! Voldemort\rquote s taken over the Ministry, what else do we need to know?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Okay, okay, it was just an idea!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They relapsed into a prickly silence. The gum-chewing waitress shuffled over and Hermione ordered two cappuccinos: As Harry was invisible, it would have looked odd to order him one. A pair of burly workmen entered the caf\'e9 and squeezed into the next booth. Hermione dropped her voice to a whisper.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I say we find a quiet place to Disapparate and head for the coun\-tryside. Once we\rquote re there, we could send a message to the Order.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Can you do that talking Patronus thing, then?\rdblquote  asked Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ve been practicing and I think so,\rdblquote  said Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, as long as it doesn\rquote t get them into trouble, though they might\rquote ve been arrested already. God, that\rquote s revolting,\rdblquote  Ron added after one sip of the foamy, grayish coffee. The waitress had heard; she shot Ron a nasty look as she shuffled off to take the new cus\-tomers\rquote  orders. The larger of the two workmen, who was blond and quite huge, now that Harry came to look at him, waved her away. She stared, affronted.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Let\rquote s get going, then, I don\rquote t want to drink this muck,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote Hermione, have you got Muggle money to pay for this?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes, I took out all my Building Society savings before I came to the Burrow. I\rquote ll bet all the change is at the bottom,\rdblquote  sighed Hermi\-one, reaching for her beaded bag.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The two workmen made identical movements, and Harry mir\-rored them without conscious thought: All three of them drew their wands. Ron, a few seconds late in realizing what was going on, lunged across the table, pushing Hermione sideways onto her bench. The force of the Death Eaters\rquote  spells shattered the tiled wall where Ron\rquote s head had just been, as Harry, still invisible, yelled, \ldblquote\i Stupefy\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The great blond Death Eater was hit in the face by a jet of red light: He slumped sideways, unconscious. His companion, unable to see who had cast the spell, fired another at Ron: Shining black ropes flew from his wand-tip and bound Ron head to foot \emdash  the waitress screamed and ran for the door \emdash  Harry sent another Stun\-ning Spell at the Death Eater with the twisted face who had tied up Ron, but the spell missed, rebounded on the window, and hit the waitress, who collapsed in front of the door.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Expulso\i0 !\rdblquote  bellowed the Death Eater, and the table behind which Harry was standing blew up: The force of the explosion slammed\lang3081  \lang1033 him into the wall and he felt his wand leave his hand as the Cloak slipped off him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Petrificus Totalus\i0 !\rdblquote  screamed Hermione from out of sight, and the Death Eater fell forward like a statue to land with a crunching thud on the mess of broken china, table, and coffee. Hermione crawled out from underneath the bench, shaking bits of glass ashtray out of her hair and trembling all over.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i D-diffindo,\i0\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 she said, pointing her wand at Ron, who roared in pain as she slashed open the knee of his jeans, leaving a deep cut. \ldblquote Oh, I\rquote m so sorry, Ron, my hand\rquote s shaking! \i Diffindo\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The severed ropes fell away. Ron got to his feet, shaking his arms to regain feeling in them. Harry picked up his wand and climbed over all the debris to where the large blond Death Eater was sprawled across the bench.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I should\rquote ve recognized him, he was there the night Dumbledore died,\rdblquote  he said. He turned over the darker Death Eater with his foot; the man\rquote s eyes moved rapidly between Harry, Ron, and Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That\rquote s Dolohov,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote I recognize him from the old wanted posters. I think the big one\rquote s Thorfinn Rowle.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Never mind what they\rquote re called!\rdblquote  said Hermione a little hysteri\-cally. \ldblquote How did they find us? What are we going to do?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Somehow her panic seemed to clear Harry\rquote s head.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Lock the door,\rdblquote  he told her, \ldblquote and Ron, turn out the lights.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He looked down at the paralyzed Dolohov, thinking fast as the lock clicked and Ron used the Deluminator to plunge the caf\'e9 into darkness. Harry could hear the men who had jeered at Hermione earlier, yelling at another girl in the distance.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What are we going to do with them?\rdblquote  Ron whispered to Harry\lang3081  \lang1033 through the dark; then, even more quietly, \ldblquote Kill them? They\rquote d kill us. They had a good go just now.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione shuddered and took a step backward. Harry shook his head.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We just need to wipe their memories,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote It\rquote s better like that, it\rquote ll throw them off the scent. If we killed them it\rquote d be obvious we were here.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re the boss,\rdblquote  said Ron, sounding profoundly relieved. \ldblquote But I\rquote ve never done a Memory Charm.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Nor have I,\rdblquote  said Hermione, \ldblquote but I know the theory.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She took a deep, calming breath, then pointed her wand at Dolo\-hov\rquote s forehead and said, \ldblquote\i Obliviate.\i0\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 At once, Dolohov\rquote s eyes became unfocused and dreamy.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Brilliant!\rdblquote  said Harry, clapping her on the back. \ldblquote Take care of the other one and the waitress while Ron and I clear up.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Clear up?\rdblquote  said Ron, looking around at the partly destroyed caf\'e9. \ldblquote Why?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t you think they might wonder what\rquote s happened if they wake up and find themselves in a place that looks like it\rquote s just been bombed?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh right, yeah \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron struggled for a moment before managing to extract his wand from his pocket.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s no wonder I can\rquote t get it out, Hermione, you packed my old jeans, they\rquote re tight.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, I\rquote m so sorry,\rdblquote  hissed Hermione, and as she dragged the waitress out of sight of the windows, Harry heard her mutter a sug\-gestion as to where Ron could stick his wand instead.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Once the caf\'e9 was restored to its previous condition, they heaved the Death Eaters back into their booth and propped them up fac\-ing each other.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But how did they find us?\rdblquote  Hermione asked, looking from one inert man to the other. \ldblquote How did they know where we were?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She turned to Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You \emdash  you don\rquote t think you\rquote ve still got your Trace on you, do you, Harry?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He can\rquote t have,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote The Trace breaks at seventeen, that\rquote s Wizarding law, you can\rquote t put it on an adult.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote As far as you know,\rdblquote  said Hermione. \ldblquote What if the Death Eaters have found a way to put it on a seventeen-year-old?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But Harry hasn\rquote t been near a Death Eater in the last twenty-four hours. Who\rquote s supposed to have put a Trace back on him?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione did not reply. Harry felt contaminated, tainted: Was that really how the Death Eaters had found them?\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote If I can\rquote t use magic, and you can\rquote t use magic near me, without us giving away our position \emdash\rdblquote  he began.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote re not splitting up!\rdblquote  said Hermione firmly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We need a safe place to hide,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote Give us time to think things through.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Grimmauld Place,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The other two gaped.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t be silly, Harry, Snape can get in there!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ron\rquote s dad said they\rquote ve put up jinxes against him \emdash  and even if they haven\rquote t worked,\rdblquote  he pressed on as Hermione began to argue, \ldblquote so what? I swear, I\rquote d like nothing better than to meet Snape!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hermione, where else is there? It\rquote s the best chance we\rquote ve got.\lang3081  \lang1033 Snape\rquote s only one Death Eater. If I\rquote ve still got the Trace on me, we\rquote ll have whole crowds of them on us wherever else we go.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She could not argue, though she looked as if she would have liked to. While she unlocked the caf\'e9 door, Ron clicked the Delumina\-tor to release the caf\'e9\rquote s light. Then, on Harry\rquote s count of three, they reversed the spells upon their three victims, and before the waitress or either of the Death Eaters could do more than stir sleepily, Harry, Ron, and Hermione had turned on the spot and vanished into the compressing darkness once more.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Seconds later Harry\rquote s lungs expanded gratefully and he opened his eyes: They were now standing in the middle of a familiar small and shabby square. Tall, dilapidated houses looked down on them from every side. Number twelve was visible to them, for they had been told of its existence by Dumbledore, its Secret-Keeper, and they rushed toward it, checking every few yards that they were not be\-ing followed or observed. They raced up the stone steps, and Harry tapped the front door once with his wand. They heard a series of metallic clicks and the clatter of a chain, then the door swung open with a creak and they hurried over the threshold.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 As Harry closed the door behind them, the old-fashioned gas lamps sprang into life, casting flickering light along the length of the hallway. It looked just as Harry remembered it: eerie, cobwebbed, the outlines of the house-elf heads on the wall throwing odd shad\-ows up the staircase. Long dark curtains concealed the portrait of Sirius\rquote s mother. The only thing that was out of place was the troll\rquote s leg umbrella stand, which was lying on its side as if Tonks had just knocked it over again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I think somebody\rquote s been in here,\rdblquote  Hermione whispered, point\-ing toward it.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That could\rquote ve happened as the Order left,\rdblquote  Ron murmured back.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So where are these jinxes they put up against Snape?\rdblquote  Harry asked.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Maybe they\rquote re only activated if he shows up?\rdblquote  suggested Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Yet they remained close together on the doormat, backs against the door, scared to move farther into the house.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, we can\rquote t stay here forever,\rdblquote  said Harry, and he took a step forward.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Severus Snape\i0 ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Mad-Eye Moody\rquote s voice whispered out of the darkness, making all three of them jump back in fright. \ldblquote We\rquote re not Snape!\rdblquote  croaked Harry, before something whooshed over him like cold air and his tongue curled backward on itself, making it impossible to speak. Before he had time to feel inside his mouth, however, his tongue had unraveled again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The other two seemed to have experienced the same unpleasant sensation. Ron was making retching noises; Hermione stammered, \ldblquote That m-must have b-been the T-Tongue-Tying Curse Mad-Eye set up for Snape!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Gingerly Harry took another step forward. Something shifted in the shadows at the end of the hall, and before any of them could say another word, a figure had risen up out of the carpet, tall, dust-colored, and terrible: Hermione screamed and so did Mrs. Black, her curtains flying open; the gray figure was gliding toward them, faster and faster, its waist-length hair and beard streaming behind it, its face sunken, fleshless, with empty eye sockets: Horribly familiar, dreadfully altered, it raised a wasted arm, pointing at Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No!\rdblquote  Harry shouted, and though he had raised his wand no spell occurred to him. \ldblquote No! It wasn\rquote t us! We didn\rquote t kill you \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 On the word \i kill,\i0  the figure exploded in a great cloud of dust: Coughing, his eyes watering, Harry looked around to see Hermione crouched on the floor by the door with her arms over her head, and Ron, who was shaking from head to foot, patting her clumsily on the shoulder and saying, \ldblquote It\rquote s all r-right. \'85 It\rquote s g-gone. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Dust swirled around Harry like mist, catching the blue gaslight, as Mrs. Black continued to scream.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Mudbloods, filth, stains of dishonor, taint of shame on the house of my fathers\i0  \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote SHUT UP!\rdblquote  Harry bellowed, directing his wand at her, and with a bang and a burst of red sparks, the curtains swung shut again, silencing her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 that was \'85\rdblquote  Hermione whimpered, as Ron helped her to her feet.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah,\rdblquote  said Harry, \ldblquote but it wasn\rquote t really him, was it? Just some\-thing to scare Snape.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Had it worked, Harry wondered, or had Snape already blasted the horror-figure aside as casually as he had killed the real Dumble\-dore? Nerves still tingling, he led the other two up the hall, half-expecting some new terror to reveal itself, but nothing moved except for a mouse skittering along the skirting board.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Before we go any farther, I think we\rquote d better check,\rdblquote  whispered Hermione, and she raised her wand and said, \ldblquote\i Homenum revelio.\i0\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Nothing happened.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, you\rquote ve just had a big shock,\rdblquote  said Ron kindly. \ldblquote What was that supposed to do?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It did what I meant it to do!\rdblquote  said Hermione rather crossly. \ldblquote That was a spell to reveal human presence, and there\rquote s nobody here except us!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And old Dusty,\rdblquote  said Ron, glancing at the patch of carpet from which the corpse-figure had risen.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Let\rquote s go up,\rdblquote  said Hermione with a frightened look at the same spot, and she led the way up the creaking stairs to the drawing room on the first floor.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione waved her wand to ignite the old gas lamps, then, shivering slightly in the drafty room, she perched on the sofa, her arms wrapped tightly around her. Ron crossed to the window and moved the heavy velvet curtain aside an inch.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Can\rquote t see anyone out there,\rdblquote  he reported. \ldblquote And you\rquote d think, if Harry still had a Trace on him, they\rquote d have followed us here. I know they can\rquote t get in the house, but \emdash  what\rquote s up, Harry?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry had given a cry of pain: His scar had burned again as some\-thing flashed across his mind like a bright light on water. He saw a large shadow and felt a fury that was not his own pound through his body, violent and brief as an electric shock.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What did you see?\rdblquote  Ron asked, advancing on Harry. \ldblquote Did you see him at my place?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, I just felt anger \emdash  he\rquote s really angry \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But that could be at the Burrow,\rdblquote  said Ron loudly. \ldblquote What else? Didn\rquote t you see anything? Was he cursing someone?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, I just felt anger \emdash  I couldn\rquote t tell \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry felt badgered, confused, and Hermione did not help as she said in a frightened voice, \ldblquote Your scar, again? But what\rquote s going on? I thought that connection had closed!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It did, for a while,\rdblquote  muttered Harry; his scar was still painful,\lang3081  \lang1033 which made it hard to concentrate. \ldblquote I \emdash  I think it\rquote s started opening again whenever he loses control, that\rquote s how it used to \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But then you\rquote ve got to close your mind!\rdblquote  said Hermione shrilly. \ldblquote Harry, Dumbledore didn\rquote t want you to use that connection, he wanted you to shut it down, that\rquote s why you were supposed to use Occlumency! Otherwise Voldemort can plant false images in your mind, remember \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, I do remember, thanks,\rdblquote  said Harry through gritted teeth; he did not need Hermione to tell him that Voldemort had once used this selfsame connection between them to lead him into a trap, nor that it had resulted in Sirius\rquote s death. He wished that he had not told them what he had seen and felt; it made Voldemort more threaten\-ing, as though he were pressing against the window of the room, and still the pain in his scar was building and he fought it: It was like resisting the urge to be sick.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He turned his back on Ron and Hermione, pretending to exam\-ine the old tapestry of the Black family tree on the wall. Then Her\-mione shrieked: Harry drew his wand again and spun around to see a silver Patronus soar through the drawing room window and land upon the floor in front of them, where it solidified into the weasel that spoke with the voice of Ron\rquote s father.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Family safe, do not reply, we are being watched.\i0\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The Patronus dissolved into nothingness. Ron let out a noise be\-tween a whimper and a groan and dropped onto the sofa: Hermione joined him, gripping his arm.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote They\rquote re all right, they\rquote re all right!\rdblquote  she whispered, and Ron half laughed and hugged her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry,\rdblquote  he said over Hermione\rquote s shoulder, \ldblquote I \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s not a problem,\rdblquote  said Harry, sickened by the pain in his head.\lang3081  \lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s your family, \rquote course you\rquote re worried. I\rquote d feel the same way.\rdblquote  He thought of Ginny. \ldblquote I \i do\i0  feel the same way.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The pain in his scar was reaching a peak, burning as it had done in the garden of the Burrow. Faintly he heard Hermione say, \ldblquote I don\rquote t want to be on my own. Could we use the sleeping bags I\rquote ve brought and camp in here tonight?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He heard Ron agree. He could not fight the pain much longer: He had to succumb.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Bathroom,\rdblquote  he muttered, and he left the room as fast as he could without running.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He barely made it: Bolting the door behind him with trembling hands, he grasped his pounding head and fell to the floor, then in an explosion of agony, he felt the rage that did not belong to him possess his soul, saw a long room lit only by firelight, and the great blond Death Eater on the floor, screaming and writhing, and a slighter figure standing over him, wand outstretched, while Harry spoke in a high, cold, merciless voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote More, Rowle, or shall we end it and feed you to Nagini? Lord Voldemort is not sure that he will forgive this time. \'85 You called me back for this, to tell me that Harry Potter has escaped again? Draco, give Rowle another taste of our displeasure. \'85 Do it, or feel my wrath yourself!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A log fell in the fire: Flames reared, their light darting across a terrified, pointed white face \emdash  with a sense of emerging from deep water, Harry drew heaving breaths and opened his eyes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He was spread-eagled on the cold black marble floor, his nose inches from one of the silver serpent tails that supported the large bathtub. He sat up. Malfoy\rquote s gaunt, petrified face seemed branded\lang3081  \lang1033 on the inside of his eyes. Harry felt sickened by what he had seen,\lang3081  \lang1033 by the use to which Draco was now being put by Voldemort.\par
There was a sharp rap on the door, and Harry jumped as Hermi\-one\rquote s voice rang out.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry, do you want your toothbrush? I\rquote ve got it here.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, great, thanks,\rdblquote  he said, fighting to keep his voice casual\lang3081  \lang1033 as he stood up to let her in.\lang3081\par
