\lang1033\ldblquote\'85 There was a boat\lang3081  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Of course there had been a boat; Harry knew the boat, ghostly green and tiny, bewitched so as to carry one wizard and one victim toward the island in the center. This, then, was how Voldemort had tested the defenses surrounding the Horcrux: by borrowing a disposable creature, a house-elf\lang3081  \lang1033\'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There was a b-basin full of potion on the island. The D-Dark Lord made Kreacher drink it. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The elf quaked from head to foot.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Kreacher drank, and as he drank, he saw terrible things. \'85 Kreacher\rquote s insides burned. \'85 Kreacher cried for Master Regulus to save him, he cried for his Mistress Black, but the Dark Lord only laughed. \'85 He made Kreacher drink all the potion. \'85 He dropped a locket into the empty basin. \'85 He filled it with more potion.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And then the Dark Lord sailed away, leaving Kreacher on the island. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry could see it happening. He watched Voldemort\rquote s white, snakelike face vanishing into darkness, those red eyes fixed piti\-lessly on the thrashing elf whose death would occur within minutes, whenever he succumbed to the desperate thirst that the burning po\-tion caused its victim. \'85 But here, Harry\rquote s imagination could go no further, for he could not see how Kreacher had escaped.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Kreacher needed water, he crawled to the island\rquote s edge and he drank from the black lake \'85 and hands, dead hands, came out of the water and dragged Kreacher under the surface. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How did you get away?\rdblquote  Harry asked, and he was not surprised to hear himself whispering.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Kreacher raised his ugly head and looked at Harry with his great, bloodshot eyes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Master Regulus told Kreacher to come back,\rdblquote  he said.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I know \emdash  but how did you escape the Inferi?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Kreacher did not seem to understand.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Master Regulus told Kreacher to come back,\rdblquote  he repeated.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I know, but \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, it\rquote s obvious, isn\rquote t it, Harry?\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote He Disappa\-rated!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But \'85 you couldn\rquote t Apparate in and out of that cave,\rdblquote  said Harry, \ldblquote otherwise Dumbledore \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Elf magic isn\rquote t like wizard\rquote s magic, is it?\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote I mean, they can Apparate and Disapparate in and out of Hogwarts when we can\rquote t.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was silence as Harry digested this. How could Voldemort have made such a mistake? But even as he thought this, Hermione spoke, and her voice was icy.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Of course, Voldemort would have considered the ways of house-elves far beneath his notice, just like all the purebloods who treat them like animals. \'85 It would never have occurred to him that they might have magic that he didn\rquote t.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The house-elf\rquote s highest law is his Master\rquote s bidding,\rdblquote  intoned Kreacher. \ldblquote Kreacher was told to come home, so Kreacher came home. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, then, you did what you were told, didn\rquote t you?\rdblquote  said Her\-mione kindly. \ldblquote You didn\rquote t disobey orders at all!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Kreacher shook his head, rocking as fast as ever.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So what happened when you got back?\rdblquote  Harry asked. \ldblquote What did Regulus say when you told him what had happened?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Master Regulus was very worried, very worried,\rdblquote  croaked Kreacher. \ldblquote Master Regulus told Kreacher to stay hidden and not to\lang3081  \lang1033 leave the house. And then \'85 it was a little while later \'85 Master Regulus came to find Kreacher in his cupboard one night, and Mas\-ter Regulus was strange, not as he usually was, disturbed in his mind, Kreacher could tell\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 and he asked Kreacher to take him to the cave, the cave where Kreacher had gone with the Dark Lord. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And so they had set off. Harry could visualize them quite clearly, the frightened old elf and the thin, dark Seeker who had so resem\-bled Sirius. \'85 Kreacher knew how to open the concealed entrance to the underground cavern, knew how to raise the tiny boat; this time it was his beloved Regulus who sailed with him to the island with its basin of poison. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And he made you drink the potion?\rdblquote  said Harry, disgusted.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Kreacher shook his head and wept. Hermione\rquote s hands leapt to her mouth: She seemed to have understood something.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote M-Master Regulus took from his pocket a locket like the one the Dark Lord had,\rdblquote  said Kreacher, tears pouring down either side of his snoutlike nose. \ldblquote And he told Kreacher to take it and, when the basin was empty, to switch the lockets. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Kreacher\rquote s sobs came in great rasps now; Harry had to concen\-trate hard to understand him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And he ordered \emdash  Kreacher to leave \emdash  without him. And he told Kreacher \emdash  to go home \emdash  and never to tell my Mistress \emdash  what he had done \emdash  but to destroy \emdash  the first locket. And he drank \emdash  all the potion \emdash  and Kreacher swapped the lockets \emdash  and watched \'85 as Master Regulus \'85 was dragged beneath the water \'85 and \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, Kreacher!\rdblquote  wailed Hermione, who was crying. She dropped to her knees beside the elf and tried to hug him. At once he was on his feet, cringing away from her, quite obviously repulsed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The Mudblood touched Kreacher, he will not allow it, what would his Mistress say?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I told you not to call her \lquote Mudblood\rquote !\rdblquote  snarled Harry, but the elf was already punishing himself: He fell to the ground and banged his forehead on the floor.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Stop him \emdash  stop him!\rdblquote  Hermione cried. \ldblquote Oh, don\rquote t you see now how sick it is, the way they\rquote ve got to obey?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Kreacher \emdash  stop, stop!\rdblquote  shouted Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The elf lay on the floor, panting and shivering, green mucus glis\-tening around his snout, a bruise already blooming on his pallid forehead where he had struck himself, his eyes swollen and blood\-shot and swimming in tears. Harry had never seen anything so pitiful.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So you brought the locket home,\rdblquote  he said relentlessly, for he was determined to know the full story. \ldblquote And you tried to destroy it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Nothing Kreacher did made any mark upon it,\rdblquote  moaned the elf. \ldblquote Kreacher tried everything, everything he knew, but nothing, nothing would work. \'85 So many powerful spells upon the casing, Kreacher was sure the way to destroy it was to get inside it, but it would not open. \'85 Kreacher punished himself, he tried again, he punished himself, he tried again. Kreacher failed to obey orders, Kreacher could not destroy the locket! And his Mistress was mad with grief, because Master Regulus had disappeared, and Kreacher could not tell her what had happened, no, because Master Regulus had f-f-forbidden him to tell any of the f-f-family what happened in the c-cave. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Kreacher began to sob so hard that there were no more coher\-ent words. Tears flowed down Hermione\rquote s cheeks as she watched Kreacher, but she did not dare touch him again. Even Ron, who was\lang3081  \lang1033 no fan of Kreacher\rquote s, looked troubled. Harry sat back on his heels and shook his head, trying to clear it.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t understand you, Kreacher,\rdblquote  he said finally. \ldblquote Voldemort tried to kill you, Regulus died to bring Voldemort down, but you were still happy to betray Sirius to Voldemort? You were happy to go to Narcissa and Bellatrix, and pass information to Voldemort through them. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry, Kreacher doesn\rquote t think like that,\rdblquote  said Hermione, wip\-ing her eyes on the back of her hand. \ldblquote He\rquote s a slave; house-elves are used to bad, even brutal treatment; what Voldemort did to Kreacher wasn\rquote t that far out of the common way. What do wizard wars mean to an elf like Kreacher? He\rquote s loyal to people who are kind to him, and Mrs. Black must have been, and Regulus certainly was, so he served them willingly and parroted their beliefs. I know what you\rquote re going to say,\rdblquote  she went on as Harry began to protest, \ldblquote that Regulus changed his mind \'85 but he doesn\rquote t seem to have explained that to Kreacher, does he? And I think I know why. Kreacher and Regulus\rquote s family were all safer if they kept to the old pure-blood line. Regulus was trying to protect them all.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Sirius \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Sirius was horrible to Kreacher, Harry, and it\rquote s no good looking like that, you know it\rquote s true. Kreacher had been alone for a long time when Sirius came to live here, and he was probably starving for a bit of affection. I\rquote m sure \lquote Miss Cissy\rquote  and \lquote Miss Bella\rquote  were perfectly lovely to Kreacher when he turned up, so he did them a favor and told them everything they wanted to know. I\rquote ve said all along that wizards would pay for how they treat house-elves. Well, Voldemort did \'85 and so did Sirius.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry had no retort. As he watched Kreacher sobbing on the\lang3081  \lang1033 floor, he remembered what Dumbledore had said to him, mere hours after Sirius\rquote s death: \i I do not think Sirius ever saw Kreacher as a being with feelings as acute as a human\rquote s. \'85\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Kreacher,\rdblquote  said Harry after a while, \ldblquote when you feel up to it, er \'85 please sit up.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It was several minutes before Kreacher hiccuped himself into si\-lence. Then he pushed himself into a sitting position again, rubbing his knuckles into his eyes like a small child.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Kreacher, I am going to ask you to do something,\rdblquote  said Harry. He glanced at Hermione for assistance. He wanted to give the order kindly, but at the same time, he could not pretend that it was not an order. However, the change in his tone seemed to have gained her approval: She smiled encouragingly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Kreacher, I want you, please, to go and find Mundungus Fletcher. We need to find out where the locket \emdash  where Master Regulus\rquote s locket is. It\rquote s really important. We want to finish the work Master Regulus started, we want to \emdash  er \emdash  ensure that he didn\rquote t die in vain.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Kreacher dropped his fists and looked up at Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Find Mundungus Fletcher?\rdblquote  he croaked.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And bring him here, to Grimmauld Place,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote Do you think you could do that for us?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 As Kreacher nodded and got to his feet, Harry had a sudden inspiration. He pulled out Hagrid\rquote s purse and took out the fake Horcrux, the substitute locket in which Regulus had placed the note to Voldemort.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Kreacher, I\rquote d, er, like you to have this,\rdblquote  he said, pressing the locket into the elf\rquote s hand. \ldblquote This belonged to Regulus and I\rquote m sure he\rquote d want you to have it as a token of gratitude for what you \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Overkill, mate,\rdblquote  said Ron as the elf took one look at the locket, let out a howl of shock and misery, and threw himself back onto the ground.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It took them nearly half an hour to calm down Kreacher, who was so overcome to be presented with a Black family heirloom for his very own that he was too weak at the knees to stand properly. When finally he was able to totter a few steps they all accompanied him to his cupboard, watched him tuck up the locket safely in his dirty blankets, and assured him that they would make its protec\-tion their first priority while he was away. He then made two low bows to Harry and Ron, and even gave a funny little spasm in Her\-mione\rquote s direction that might have been an attempt at a respectful salute, before Disapparating with the usual loud \i crack.\lang3081\i0\par
