THE DEATH OF ALBUS DUMBLEDORE\lang3081\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi284\qj\lang1033\par
Ron and Hermione gave roars of outrage, but Harry said noth\-ing. He pushed the newspaper away; he did not want to read any more: He knew what it would say. Nobody but those who had been on top of the tower when Dumbledore died knew who had really killed him and, as Rita Skeeter had already told the Wizarding world, Harry had been seen running from the place moments after Dumbledore had fallen.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m sorry, Harry,\rdblquote  Lupin said.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So Death Eaters have taken over the \i Daily Prophet\i0  too?\rdblquote  asked Hermione furiously.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lupin nodded.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But surely people realize what\rquote s going on?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The coup has been smooth and virtually silent,\rdblquote  said Lupin.\lang3081  \lang1033\ldblquote The official version of Scrimgeour\rquote s murder is that he resigned; he has been replaced by Pius Thicknesse, who is under the Imperius Curse.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Why didn\rquote t Voldemort declare himself Minister of Magic?\rdblquote  asked Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lupin laughed.\lang3081\par
