\lang1033\ldblquote What, has she got magic ears as well as an eye, now?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The witch glanced toward the shining mahogany door facing the space full of pamphlet-makers; Harry looked too, and rage reared in him like a snake. Where there might have been a peephole on a Muggle front door, a large, round eye with a bright blue iris had been set into the wood \emdash  an eye that was shockingly familiar to anybody who had known Alastor Moody.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 For a split second Harry forgot where he was and what he was\lang3081  \lang1033 doing there: He even forgot that he was invisible. He strode straight over to the door to examine the eye. It was not moving: It gazed blindly upward, frozen. The plaque beneath it read:\par
\par
\pard\qc DOLORES UMBRIDGE\lang3081\par
\lang1033 SENIOR UNDERSECRETARY TO THE MINISTER\lang3081\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi284\qj\lang1033\par
Below that, a slightly shinier new plaque read:\par
\par
\pard\qc HEAD OF THE MUGGLE-BORN\par
REGISTRATION COMMISSION\lang3081\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi284\qj\lang1033\par
Harry looked back at the dozen pamphlet-makers: Though they were intent upon their work, he could hardly suppose that they would not notice if the door of an empty office opened in front of them. He therefore withdrew from an inner pocket an odd object with little waving legs and a rubber-bulbed horn for a body. Crouching down beneath the Cloak, he placed the Decoy Detonator on the ground.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It scuttled away at once through the legs of the witches and wiz\-ards in front of him. A few moments later, during which Harry waited with his hand upon the doorknob, there came a loud bang and a great deal of acrid black smoke billowed from a corner. The young witch in the front row shrieked: Pink pages flew everywhere as she and her fellows jumped up, looking around for the source of the commotion. Harry turned the doorknob, stepped into Um\-bridge\rquote s office, and closed the door behind him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He felt he had stepped back in time. The room was exactly like Umbridge\rquote s office at Hogwarts: Lace draperies, doilies, and dried flowers covered every available surface. The walls bore the same\lang3081  \lang1033 ornamental plates, each featuring a highly colored, beribboned kit\-ten, gamboling and frisking with sickening cuteness. The desk was covered with a flouncy, flowered cloth. Behind Mad-Eye\rquote s eye, a telescopic attachment enabled Umbridge to spy on the workers on the other side of the door. Harry took a look through it and saw that they were all still gathered around the Decoy Detonator. He wrenched the telescope out of the door, leaving a hole behind, pulled the magical eyeball out of it, and placed it in his pocket. Then he turned to face the room again, raised his wand, and murmured, \ldblquote\i Accio Locket.\i0\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Nothing happened, but he had not expected it to; no doubt Um\-bridge knew all about protective charms and spells. He therefore hurried behind her desk and began pulling open the drawers. He saw quills and notebooks and Spellotape; enchanted paper clips that coiled snakelike from their drawer and had to be beaten back; a fussy little lace box full of spare hair bows and clips; but no sign of a locket.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a filing cabinet behind the desk: Harry set to search\-ing it. Like Filch\rquote s filing cabinets at Hogwarts, it was full of fold\-ers, each labeled with a name. It was not until Harry reached the bottommost drawer that he saw something to distract him from his search: Mr. Weasley\rquote s file.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He pulled it out and opened it.\par
