\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah,\rdblquote  said Ron sycophantically, \ldblquote that makes sense.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, it doesn\rquote t,\rdblquote  snapped Hermione, \ldblquote but I still think we ought to talk to Mr. Lovegood. A symbol that links Dumbledore, Grin\-delwald, and Godric\rquote s Hollow? Harry, I\rquote m sure we ought to know about this!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I think we should vote on it,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote Those in favor of going to see Lovegood \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 His hand flew into the air before Hermione\rquote s. Her lips quivered suspiciously as she raised her own.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Outvoted, Harry, sorry,\rdblquote  said Ron, clapping him on the back.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Fine,\rdblquote  said Harry, half amused, half irritated. \ldblquote Only, once we\rquote ve seen Lovegood, let\rquote s try and look for some more Horcruxes, shall we? Where do the Lovegoods live, anyway? Do either of you know?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, they\rquote re not far from my place,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote I dunno exactly where, but Mum and Dad always point toward the hills whenever they mention them. Shouldn\rquote t be hard to find.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
