\lang1033 Harry and the others were shoved and kicked up broad stone steps into a hallway lined with portraits.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Follow me,\rdblquote  said Narcissa, leading the way across the hall. \ldblquote My son, Draco, is home for his Easter holidays. If that is Harry Potter, he will know.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The drawing room dazzled after the darkness outside; even with his eyes almost closed Harry could make out the wide proportions of the room. A crystal chandelier hung from the ceiling, more por\-traits against the dark purple walls. Two figures rose from chairs in front of an ornate marble fireplace as the prisoners were forced into the room by the Snatchers.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What is this?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The dreadfully familiar, drawling voice of Lucius Malfoy fell on Harry\rquote s ears. He was panicking now: He could see no way out, and it was easier, as his fear mounted, to block out Voldemort\rquote s thoughts, though his scar was still burning.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote They say they\rquote ve got Potter,\rdblquote  said Narcissa\rquote s cold voice. \ldblquote Draco, come here.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry did not dare look directly at Draco, but saw him obliquely: a figure slightly taller than he was, rising from an armchair, his face a pale and pointed blur beneath white-blond hair.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Greyback forced the prisoners to turn again so as to place Harry directly beneath the chandelier.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, boy?\rdblquote  rasped the werewolf.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry was facing a mirror over the fireplace, a great gilded thing in an intricately scrolled frame. Through the slits of his eyes he saw his own reflection for the first time since leaving Grimmauld Place.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 His face was huge, shiny, and pink, every feature distorted by Hermione\rquote s jinx. His black hair reached his shoulders and there was a dark shadow around his jaw. Had he not known that it was he who stood there, he would have wondered who was wearing his glasses. He resolved not to speak, for his voice was sure to give him away; yet he still avoided eye contact with Draco as the latter approached.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, Draco?\rdblquote  said Lucius Malfoy. He sounded avid. \ldblquote Is it? Is it Harry Potter?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
