\lang1033 His gray eyes raked Harry\rquote s forehead.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There\rquote s something there,\rdblquote  he whispered, \ldblquote it could be the scar,\lang3081  \lang1033 stretched tight. \'85 Draco, come here, look properly! What do you think?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry saw Draco\rquote s face up close now, right beside his father\rquote s. They were extraordinarily alike, except that while his father looked beside himself with excitement, Draco\rquote s expression was full of re\-luctance, even fear.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t know,\rdblquote  he said, and he walked away toward the fireplace where his mother stood watching.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We had better be certain, Lucius,\rdblquote  Narcissa called to her hus\-band in her cold, clear voice. \ldblquote Completely sure that it is Potter, before we summon the Dark Lord \'85 They say this is his\rdblquote  \emdash  she was looking closely at the blackthorn wand \emdash  \ldblquote but it does not re\-semble Ollivander\rquote s description. \'85 If we are mistaken, if we call the Dark Lord here for nothing \'85 Remember what he did to Rowle and Dolohov?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What about the Mudblood, then?\rdblquote  growled Greyback. Harry was nearly thrown off his feet as the Snatchers forced the prisoners to swivel around again, so that the light fell on Hermione instead.\lang3081\par
