\lang1033\ldblquote Begging your pardon, \i Mr.\i0  Malfoy,\rdblquote  interjected Greyback, \ldblquote but it\rquote s us that caught Potter, and it\rquote s us that\rquote ll be claiming the gold \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Gold!\rdblquote  laughed Bellatrix, still attempting to throw off her\lang3081  \lang1033 brother-in-law, her free hand groping in her pocket for her wand. \ldblquote Take your gold, filthy scavenger, what do I want with gold? I seek only the honor of his \emdash  of\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She stopped struggling, her dark eyes fixed upon something Harry could not see. Jubilant at her capitulation, Lucius threw her hand from him and ripped up his own sleeve \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote STOP!\rdblquote  shrieked Bellatrix. \ldblquote Do not touch it, we shall all perish if the Dark Lord comes now!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lucius froze, his index finger hovering over his own Mark. Bel\-latrix strode out of Harry\rquote s limited line of vision.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What is that?\rdblquote  he heard her say.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Sword,\rdblquote  grunted an out-of-sight Snatcher.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Give it to me.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s not yorn, missus, it\rquote s mine, I reckon I found it.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a bang and a flash of red light: Harry knew that the Snatcher had been Stunned. There was a roar of anger from his fel\-lows: Scabior drew his wand.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What d\rquote you think you\rquote re playing at, woman?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Stupefy\i0 !\rdblquote  she screamed. \ldblquote\i Stupefy\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They were no match for her, even though there were four of them against one of her: She was a witch, as Harry knew, with prodi\-gious skill and no conscience. They fell where they stood, all except Greyback, who had been forced into a kneeling position, his arms outstretched. Out of the corners of his eyes Harry saw Bellatrix bearing down upon the werewolf, the sword of Gryffindor gripped tightly in her hand, her face waxen.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Where did you get this sword?\rdblquote  she whispered to Greyback as she pulled his wand out of his unresisting grip.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How dare you?\rdblquote  he snarled, his mouth the only thing that could\lang3081  \lang1033 move as he was forced to gaze up at her. He bared his pointed teeth. \ldblquote Release me, woman!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Where did you find this sword?\rdblquote  she repeated, brandishing it in his face. \ldblquote Snape sent it to my vault in Gringotts!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It was in their tent,\rdblquote  rasped Greyback. \ldblquote Release me, I say!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She waved her wand, and the werewolf sprang to his feet, but ap\-peared too wary to approach her. He prowled behind an armchair, his filthy curved nails clutching its back.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Draco, move this scum outside,\rdblquote  said Bellatrix, indicating the unconscious men. \ldblquote If you haven\rquote t got the guts to finish them, then leave them in the courtyard for me.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t you dare speak to Draco like \emdash\rdblquote  said Narcissa furiously, but Bellatrix screamed,\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Be quiet! The situation is graver than you can possibly imagine, Cissy! We have a very serious problem!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She stood, panting slightly, looking down at the sword, examin\-ing its hilt. Then she turned to look at the silent prisoners.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote If it is indeed Potter, he must not be harmed,\rdblquote  she muttered, more to herself than to the others. \ldblquote The Dark Lord wishes to dis\-pose of Potter himself. \'85 But if he finds out\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 I must\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 I must know. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She turned back to her sister again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The prisoners must be placed in the cellar, while I think what to do!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote This is my house, Bella, you don\rquote t give orders in my \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Do it! You have no idea of the danger we are in!\rdblquote  shrieked Bel\-latrix. She looked frightening, mad; a thin stream of fire issued from her wand and burned a hole in the carpet.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Narcissa hesitated for a moment, then addressed the werewolf.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Take these prisoners down to the cellar, Greyback.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Wait,\rdblquote  said Bellatrix sharply. \ldblquote All except\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 except for the Mudblood.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Greyback gave a grunt of pleasure.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No!\rdblquote  shouted Ron. \ldblquote You can have me, keep me!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Bellatrix hit him across the face; the blow echoed around the room.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote If she dies under questioning, I\rquote ll take you next,\rdblquote  she said. \ldblquote Blood traitor is next to Mudblood in my book. Take them downstairs, Greyback, and make sure they are secure, but do nothing more to them \emdash  yet.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She threw Greyback\rquote s wand back to him, then took a short silver knife from under her robes. She cut Hermione free from the other prisoners, then dragged her by the hair into the middle of the room, while Greyback forced the rest of them to shuffle across to another door, into a dark passageway, his wand held out in front of him, projecting an invisible and irresistible force.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Reckon she\rquote ll let me have a bit of the girl when she\rquote s finished with her?\rdblquote  Greyback crooned as he forced them along the corridor. \ldblquote I\rquote d say I\rquote ll get a bite or two, wouldn\rquote t you, ginger?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry could feel Ron shaking. They were forced down a steep flight of stairs, still tied back-to-back and in danger of slipping and breaking their necks at any moment. At the bottom was a heavy door. Greyback unlocked it with a tap of his wand, then forced them into a dank and musty room and left them in total darkness. The echoing bang of the slammed cellar door had not died away before there was a terrible, drawn-out scream from directly above them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote HERMIONE!\rdblquote  Ron bellowed, and he started to writhe and\lang3081  \lang1033 struggle against the ropes tying them together, so that Harry stag\-gered. \ldblquote HERMIONE!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Be quiet!\rdblquote  Harry said. \ldblquote Shut up, Ron, we need to work out a way \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote HERMIONE! HERMIONE!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We need a plan, stop yelling \emdash  we need to get these ropes off\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry?\rdblquote  came a whisper through the darkness. \ldblquote Ron? Is that you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron stopped shouting. There was a sound of movement close by them, then Harry saw a shadow moving closer.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry? Ron?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Luna\i0 ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes, it\rquote s me! Oh no, I didn\rquote t want you to be caught!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Luna, can you help us get these ropes off?\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh yes, I expect so. \'85 There\rquote s an old nail we use if we need to break anything. \'85 Just a moment\lang3081  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione screamed again from overhead, and they could hear Bellatrix screaming too, but her words were inaudible, for Ron shouted again, \ldblquote HERMIONE! HERMIONE!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Mr. Ollivander?\rdblquote  Harry could hear Luna saying. \ldblquote Mr. Olli\-vander, have you got the nail? If you just move over a little bit\'85 I think it was beside the water jug. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She was back within seconds.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote ll need to stay still,\rdblquote  she said.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry could feel her digging at the rope\rquote s tough fibers to work the knots free. From upstairs they heard Bellatrix\rquote s voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m going to ask you again! Where did you get this sword? \i Where\i0 ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We found it \emdash  we found it \emdash  PLEASE!\rdblquote  Hermione screamed again; Ron struggled harder than ever, and the rusty nail slipped onto Harry\rquote s wrist.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ron, please stay still!\rdblquote  Luna whispered. \ldblquote I can\rquote t see what I\rquote m doing \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote My pocket!\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote In my pocket, there\rquote s a Deluminator, and it\rquote s full of light!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A few seconds later, there was a click, and the luminescent spheres the Deluminator had sucked from the lamps in the tent flew into the cellar: Unable to rejoin their sources, they simply hung there, like tiny suns, flooding the underground room with light. Harry saw Luna, all eyes in her white face, and the motionless figure of Ollivander the wandmaker, curled up on the floor in the corner. Craning around, he caught sight of their fellow prisoners: Dean and Griphook the goblin, who seemed barely conscious, kept standing by the ropes that bound him to the humans.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, that\rquote s much easier, thanks, Ron,\rdblquote  said Luna, and she began hacking at their bindings again. \ldblquote Hello, Dean!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 From above came Bellatrix\rquote s voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You are lying, filthy Mudblood, and I know it! You have been inside my vault at Gringotts! Tell the truth, \i tell the truth\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Another terrible scream \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote HERMIONE!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What else did you take? What else have you got? Tell me the truth or, I swear, I shall run you through with this knife!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry felt the ropes fall away and turned, rubbing his wrists, to see Ron running around the cellar, looking up at the low ceiling, searching for a trapdoor. Dean, his face bruised and bloody, said\lang3081  \lang1033\ldblquote Thanks\rdblquote  to Luna and stood there, shivering, but Griphook sank onto the cellar floor, looking groggy and disoriented, many welts across his swarthy face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron was now trying to Disapparate without a wand.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There\rquote s no way out, Ron,\rdblquote  said Luna, watching his fruitless ef\-forts. \ldblquote The cellar is completely escape-proof. I tried, at first. Mr. Ol\-livander has been here for a long time, he\rquote s tried everything.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione was screaming again: The sound went through Harry like physical pain. Barely conscious of the fierce prickling of his scar, he too started to run around the cellar, feeling the walls for he hardly knew what, knowing in his heart that it was useless.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What else did you take, what else? ANSWER ME! \i CRUCIO\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione\rquote s screams echoed off the walls upstairs, Ron was half sobbing as he pounded the walls with his fists, and Harry in utter desperation seized Hagrid\rquote s pouch from around his neck and groped inside it: He pulled out Dumbledore\rquote s Snitch and shook it, hoping for he did not know what \emdash  nothing happened \emdash  he waved the broken halves of the phoenix wand, but they were lifeless \emdash  the mirror fragment fell sparkling to the floor, and he saw a gleam of brightest blue \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Dumbledore\rquote s eye was gazing at him out of the mirror.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Help us!\rdblquote  he yelled at it in mad desperation. \ldblquote We\rquote re in the cellar of Malfoy Manor, help us!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The eye blinked and was gone.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry was not even sure that it had really been there. He tilted the shard of mirror this way and that, and saw nothing reflected there but the walls and ceiling of their prison, and upstairs Hermione was screaming worse than ever, and next to him Ron was bellowing, \ldblquote HERMIONE! HERMIONE!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How did you get into my vault?\rdblquote  they heard Bellatrix scream. \ldblquote Did that dirty little goblin in the cellar help you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We only met him tonight!\rdblquote  Hermione sobbed. \ldblquote We\rquote ve never been inside your vault. \'85 It isn\rquote t the real sword! It\rquote s a copy, just a copy!\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote A copy?\rdblquote  screeched Bellatrix. \ldblquote Oh, a likely story!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But we can find out easily!\rdblquote  came Lucius\rquote s voice. \ldblquote Draco, fetch the goblin, he can tell us whether the sword is real or not!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry dashed across the cellar to where Griphook was huddled on the floor.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Griphook,\rdblquote  he whispered into the goblin\rquote s pointed ear, \ldblquote you must tell them that sword\rquote s a fake, they mustn\rquote t know it\rquote s the real one, Griphook, please \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He could hear someone scuttling down the cellar steps; next mo\-ment, Draco\rquote s shaking voice spoke from behind the door.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Stand back. Line up against the back wall. Don\rquote t try anything, or I\rquote ll kill you!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They did as they were bidden; as the lock turned, Ron clicked the Deluminator and the lights whisked back into his pocket, restoring the cellar\rquote s darkness. The door flew open; Malfoy marched inside, wand held out in front of him, pale and determined. He seized the little goblin by the arm and backed out again, dragging Griphook with him. The door slammed shut and at the same moment a loud \i crack\i0  echoed inside the cellar.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron clicked the Deluminator. Three balls of light flew back into the air from his pocket, revealing Dobby the house-elf, who had just Apparated into their midst.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote DOB \emdash  !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry hit Ron on the arm to stop him shouting, and Ron looked\lang3081  \lang1033 terrified at his mistake. Footsteps crossed the ceiling overhead: Draco marching Griphook to Bellatrix.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Dobby\rquote s enormous, tennis-ball-shaped eyes were wide; he was trembling from his feet to the tips of his ears. He was back in the home of his old masters, and it was clear that he was petrified.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry Potter,\rdblquote  he squeaked in the tiniest quiver of a voice, \ldblquote Dobby has come to rescue you.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But how did you \emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 An awful scream drowned Harry\rquote s words: Hermione was being tortured again. He cut to the essentials.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You can Disapparate out of this cellar?\rdblquote  he asked Dobby, who nodded, his ears flapping.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And you can take humans with you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Dobby nodded again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Right. Dobby, I want you to grab Luna, Dean, and Mr. Olli\-vander, and take them \emdash  take them to \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Bill and Fleur\rquote s,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote Shell Cottage on the outskirts of Tinworth!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The elf nodded for a third time.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And then come back,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote Can you do that, Dobby?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Of course, Harry Potter,\rdblquote  whispered the little elf. He hurried over to Mr. Ollivander, who appeared to be barely conscious. He took one of the wandmaker\rquote s hands in his own, then held out the other to Luna and Dean, neither of whom moved.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry, we want to help you!\rdblquote  Luna whispered.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We can\rquote t leave you here,\rdblquote  said Dean.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Go, both of you! We\rquote ll see you at Bill and Fleur\rquote s.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
