It was just possible to discern Ron under his disguise, but only, Harry thought, because he knew him so well. Ron\rquote s hair was now long and wavy; he had a thick brown beard and mustache, no freck\-les, a short, broad nose, and heavy eyebrows.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, he\rquote s not my type, but he\rquote ll do,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote Shall we go, then?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 All three of them glanced back at Shell Cottage, lying dark and silent under the fading stars, then turned and began to walk toward\lang3081  \lang1033 the point, just beyond the boundary wall, where the Fidelius Charm stopped working and they would be able to Disapparate. Once past the gate, Griphook spoke.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I should climb up now, Harry Potter, I think?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry bent down and the goblin clambered onto his back, his hands linked in front of Harry\rquote s throat. He was not heavy, but Harry disliked the feeling of the goblin and the surprising strength with which he clung on. Hermione pulled the Invisibility Cloak out of the beaded bag and threw it over them both.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Perfect,\rdblquote  she said, bending down to check Harry\rquote s feet. \ldblquote I can\rquote t see a thing. Let\rquote s go.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry turned on the spot, with Griphook on his shoulders, con\-centrating with all his might on the Leaky Cauldron, the inn that was the entrance to Diagon Alley. The goblin clung even tighter as they moved into the compressing darkness, and seconds later Harry\rquote s feet found pavement and he opened his eyes on Charing Cross Road. Muggles bustled past wearing the hangdog expressions of early morning, quite unconscious of the little inn\rquote s existence.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The bar of the Leaky Cauldron was nearly deserted. Tom, the stooped and toothless landlord, was polishing glasses behind the bar counter; a couple of warlocks having a muttered conversation in the far corner glanced at Hermione and drew back into the shadows.\lang3081\par
