\lang1033 Harry felt Griphook\rquote s clasped hands tighten momentarily around his neck.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Shall we?\rdblquote  said Travers, gesturing Hermione forward.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione had no choice but to fall into step beside him and head along the crooked, cobbled street toward the place where the snowy-white Gringotts stood towering over the other little shops. Ron sloped along beside them, and Harry and Griphook followed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A watchful Death Eater was the very last thing they needed, and the worst of it was, with Travers marching at what he believed to be Bellatrix\rquote s side, there was no means for Harry to communicate with Hermione or Ron. All too soon they arrived at the foot of the\lang3081  \lang1033 marble steps leading up to the great bronze doors. As Griphook had already warned them, the liveried goblins who usually flanked the entrance had been replaced by two wizards, both of whom were clutching long thin golden rods.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ah, Probity Probes,\rdblquote  sighed Travers theatrically, \ldblquote so crude \emdash  but effective!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And he set off up the steps, nodding left and right to the wiz\-ards, who raised the golden rods and passed them up and down his body. The Probes, Harry knew, detected spells of concealment and hidden magical objects. Knowing that he had only seconds; Harry pointed Draco\rquote s wand at each of the guards in turn and murmured, \ldblquote\i Confundo\i0\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 twice. Unnoticed by Travers, who was looking through the bronze doors at the inner hall, each of the guards gave a little start as the spells hit them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione\rquote s long black hair rippled behind her as she climbed the steps.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote One moment, madam,\rdblquote  said the guard, raising his Probe.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But you\rquote ve just done that!\rdblquote  said Hermione in Bellatrix\rquote s com\-manding, arrogant voice. Travers looked around, eyebrows raised. The guard was confused. He stared down at the thin golden Probe and then at his companion, who said in a slightly dazed voice,\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, you\rquote ve just checked them, Marius.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione swept forward, Ron by her side, Harry and Griphook trotting invisibly behind them. Harry glanced back as they crossed the threshold: The wizards were both scratching their heads.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Two goblins stood before the inner doors, which were made of silver and which carried the poem warning of dire retribution to potential thieves. Harry looked up at it, and all of a sudden a knife-sharp memory came to him: standing on this very spot on the day\lang3081  \lang1033 that he had turned eleven, the most wonderful birthday of his life, and Hagrid standing beside him saying, \ldblquote\i Like I said, yeh\rquote d be mad ter try an\rquote  rob it.\i0\rdblquote  Gringotts had seemed a place of wonder that day, the enchanted repository of a trove of gold he had never known he possessed, and never for an instant could he have dreamed that he would return to steal. \'85 But within seconds they were standing in the vast marble hall of the bank.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The long counter was manned by goblins sitting on high stools, serving the first customers of the day. Hermione, Ron, and Travers headed toward an old goblin who was examining a thick gold coin through an eyeglass. Hermione allowed Travers to step ahead of her on the pretext of explaining features of the hall to Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The goblin tossed the coin he was holding aside, said to nobody in particular, \ldblquote Leprechaun,\rdblquote  and then greeted Travers, who passed over a tiny golden key, which was examined and given back to him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione stepped forward.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Madam Lestrange!\rdblquote  said the goblin, evidently startled. \ldblquote Dear me! How \emdash  how may I help you today?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\ldblquote I \lang1033 wish to enter my vault,\rdblquote  said Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The old goblin seemed to recoil a little. Harry glanced around. Not only was Travers hanging back, watching, but several other goblins had looked up from their work to stare at Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You have \'85 identification?\rdblquote  asked the goblin.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Identification? I \emdash  I have never been asked for identification before!\rdblquote  said Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i They know\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 whispered Griphook in Harry\rquote s ear. \ldblquote\i They must have been warned there might be an impostor\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Your wand will do, madam,\rdblquote  said the goblin. He held out a slightly trembling hand, and in a dreadful blast of realization Harry\lang3081  \lang1033 knew that the goblins of Gringotts were aware that Bellatrix\rquote s wand had been stolen.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Act now, act now,\i0\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 whispered Griphook in Harry\rquote s ear, \ldblquote\i the Im\-perius Curse\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry raised the hawthorn wand beneath the cloak, pointed it at the old goblin, and whispered, for the first time in his life, \ldblquote\i Imperio\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A curious sensation shot down Harry\rquote s arm, a feeling of tingling warmth that seemed to flow from his mind, down the sinews and veins connecting him to the wand and the curse it had just cast. The goblin took Bellatrix\rquote s wand, examined it closely, and then said, \ldblquote Ah, you have had a new wand made, Madam Lestrange!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What?\rdblquote  said Hermione. \ldblquote No, no, that\rquote s mine \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote A new wand?\rdblquote  said Travers, approaching the counter again; still the goblins all around were watching. \ldblquote But how could you have done, which wandmaker did you use?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
