\lang1033\ldblquote Just look around!\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote Remember, the cup\rquote s small and gold, it\rquote s got a badger engraved on it, two handles \emdash  otherwise see if you can spot Ravenclaw\rquote s symbol anywhere, the eagle \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They directed their wands into every nook and crevice, turning cautiously on the spot. It was impossible not to brush up against anything; Harry sent a great cascade of fake Galleons onto the ground where they joined the goblets, and now there was scarcely room to place their feet, and the glowing gold blazed with heat, so that the vault felt like a furnace. Harry\rquote s wandlight passed over shields and goblin-made helmets set on shelves rising to the ceiling; higher and higher he raised the beam, until suddenly it found an object that made his heart skip and his hand tremble.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i It\rquote s there, it\rquote s up there\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron and Hermione pointed their wands at it too, so that the little golden cup sparkled in a three-way spotlight: the cup that had be\-longed to Helga Hufflepuff, which had passed into the possession of Hepzibah Smith, from whom it had been stolen by Tom Riddle.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And how the hell are we going to get up there without touching anything?\rdblquote  asked Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Accio Cup\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 cried Hermione, who had evidently forgotten in her desperation what Griphook had told them during their planning sessions.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No use, no use!\rdblquote  snarled the goblin.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Then what do we do?\rdblquote  said Harry, glaring at the goblin. \ldblquote If you want the sword, Griphook, then you\rquote ll have to help us more than \emdash  wait! Can I touch stuff with the sword? Hermione, give it here!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione fumbled inside her robes, drew out the beaded bag, rummaged for a few seconds, then removed the shining sword. Harry seized it by its rubied hilt and touched the tip of the blade to a silver flagon nearby, which did not multiply.\lang3081\par
