\lang1033\ldblquote They \i what\i0 ?\rdblquote  said Harry, Ron, and Hermione together.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah,\rdblquote  said Neville, panting a little now, because the passage was climbing so steeply, \ldblquote well, you can see their thinking. It had worked really well, kidnapping kids to force their relatives to behave,\lang3081  \lang1033 I s\rquote pose it was only a matter of time before they did it the other way around. Thing was,\rdblquote  he faced them, and Harry was astonished to see that he was grinning, \ldblquote they bit off a bit more than they could chew with Gran. Little old witch living alone, they probably thought they didn\rquote t need to send anyone particularly powerful. Anyway,\rdblquote  Neville laughed, \ldblquote Dawlish is still in St. Mungo\rquote s and Gran\rquote s on the run. She sent me a letter,\rdblquote  he clapped a hand to the breast pocket of his robes, \ldblquote telling me she was proud of me, that I\rquote m my parents\rquote  son, and to keep it up.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Cool,\rdblquote  said Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah,\rdblquote  said Neville happily. \ldblquote Only thing was, once they realized they had no hold over me, they decided Hogwarts could do without me after all. I don\rquote t know whether they were planning to kill me or send me to Azkaban; either way, I knew it was time to disappear.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But,\rdblquote  said Ron, looking thoroughly confused, \ldblquote aren\rquote t \emdash  aren\rquote t we heading straight back into Hogwarts?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \rquote Course,\rdblquote  said Neville. \ldblquote You\rquote ll see. We\rquote re here.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They turned a corner and there ahead of them was the end of the passage. Another short flight of steps led to a door just like the one hidden behind Ariana\rquote s portrait. Neville pushed it open and climbed through. As Harry followed, he heard Neville call out to unseen people:\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Look who it is! Didn\rquote t I tell you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 As Harry emerged into the room beyond the passage, there were several screams and yells: \ldblquote HARRY!\rdblquote  \ldblquote It\rquote s Potter, it\rquote s POTTER!\rdblquote  \ldblquote Ron!\rdblquote  \ldblquote\i Hermione\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He had a confused impression of colored hangings, of lamps and many faces. The next moment, he, Ron, and Hermione were en\-gulfed, hugged, pounded on the back, their hair ruffled, their hands\lang3081  \lang1033 shaken, by what seemed to be more than twenty people: They might just have won a Quidditch final.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Okay, okay, calm down!\rdblquote  Neville called, and as the crowd backed away, Harry was able to take in their surroundings.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He did not recognize the room at all. It was enormous, and looked rather like the interior of a particularly sumptuous tree house, or perhaps a gigantic ship\rquote s cabin. Multicolored hammocks were strung from the ceiling and from a balcony that ran around the dark wood-paneled and windowless walls, which were covered in bright tapestry hangings: Harry saw the gold Gryffindor lion, emblazoned on scarlet; the black badger of Hufflepuff, set against yellow; and the bronze eagle of Ravenclaw, on blue. The silver and green of Slytherin alone were absent. There were bulging bookcases, a few broomsticks propped against the walls, and in the corner, a large wooden-cased wireless.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Where are we?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Room of Requirement, of course!\rdblquote  said Neville. \ldblquote Surpassed it\-self, hasn\rquote t it? The Carrows were chasing me, and I knew I had just one chance for a hideout: I managed to get through the door and this is what I found! Well, it wasn\rquote t exactly like this when I arrived, it was a load smaller, there was only one hammock and just Gryf\-findor hangings. But it\rquote s expanded as more and more of the D.A. have arrived.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And the Carrows can\rquote t get in?\rdblquote  asked Harry, looking around for the door.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said Seamus Finnigan, whom Harry had not recognized until he spoke: Seamus\rquote s face was bruised and puffy. \ldblquote It\rquote s a proper hideout, as long as one of us stays in here, they can\rquote t get at us, the door won\rquote t open. It\rquote s all down to Neville. He really \i gets\i0  this room.\lang3081  \lang1033 You\rquote ve got to ask it for \i exactly\i0  what you need \emdash  like, \lquote I don\rquote t want any Carrow supporters to be able to get in\rquote  \emdash  and it\rquote ll do it for you! You\rquote ve just got to make sure you close the loopholes! Neville\rquote s the man!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s quite straightforward, really,\rdblquote  said Neville modestly. \ldblquote I\rquote d been in here about a day and a half, and getting really hungry, and wishing I could get something to eat, and that\rquote s when the passage to the Hog\rquote s Head opened up. I went through it and met Aberforth. He\rquote s been providing us with food, because for some reason, that\rquote s the one thing the room doesn\rquote t really do.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, well, food\rquote s one of the five exceptions to Gamp\rquote s Law of Elemental Transfiguration,\rdblquote  said Ron to general astonishment.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So we\rquote ve been hiding out here for nearly two weeks,\rdblquote  said Sea\-mus, \ldblquote and it just makes more hammocks every time we need them, and it even sprouted a pretty good bathroom once girls started turning up \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\emdash  and thought they\rquote d quite like to wash, yes,\rdblquote  supplied Lav\-ender Brown, whom Harry had not noticed until that point. Now that he looked around properly, he recognized many familiar faces. Both Patil twins were there, as were Terry Boot, Ernie Macmillan, Anthony Goldstein, and Michael Corner.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Tell us what you\rquote ve been up to, though,\rdblquote  said Ernie. \ldblquote There\rquote ve been so many rumors, we\rquote ve been trying to keep up with you on \i Potterwatch.\i0\rdblquote  He pointed at the wireless. \ldblquote You didn\rquote t break into Gringotts?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote They did!\rdblquote  said Neville. \ldblquote And the dragon\rquote s true too!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a smattering of applause and a few whoops; Ron took a bow.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What were you after?\rdblquote  asked Seamus eagerly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Before any of them could parry the question with one of their own, Harry felt a terrible, scorching pain in the lightning scar. As he turned his back hastily on the curious and delighted faces, the Room of Requirement vanished, and he was standing inside a ru\-ined stone shack, and the rotting floorboards were ripped apart at his feet, a disinterred golden box lay open and empty beside the hole, and Voldemort\rquote s scream of fury vibrated inside his head.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 With an enormous effort he pulled out of Voldemort\rquote s mind again, back to where he stood, swaying, in the Room of Require\-ment, sweat pouring from his face and Ron holding him up.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Are you all right, Harry?\rdblquote  Neville was saying. \ldblquote Want to sit down? I expect you\rquote re tired, aren\rquote t \emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said Harry. He looked at Ron and Hermione, trying to tell them without words that Voldemort had just discovered the loss of one of the other Horcruxes. Time was running out fast: If Volde\-mort chose to visit Hogwarts next, they would miss their chance.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We need to get going,\rdblquote  he said, and their expressions told him that they understood.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What are we going to do, then, Harry?\rdblquote  asked Seamus. \ldblquote What\rquote s the plan?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Plan?\rdblquote  repeated Harry. He was exercising all his willpower to prevent himself succumbing again to Voldemort\rquote s rage: His scar was still burning. \ldblquote Well, there\rquote s something we \emdash  Ron, Hermione, and I \emdash  need to do, and then we\rquote ll get out of here.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Nobody was laughing or whooping anymore. Neville looked confused.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What d\rquote you mean, \lquote get out of here\rquote ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We haven\rquote t come back to stay,\rdblquote  said Harry, rubbing his scar, trying to soothe the pain. \ldblquote There\rquote s something important we need to do \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What is it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I \emdash  I can\rquote t tell you.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a ripple of muttering at this: Neville\rquote s brows contracted.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Why can\rquote t you tell us? It\rquote s something to do with fighting You-Know-Who, right?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, yeah \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Then we\rquote ll help you.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The other members of Dumbledore\rquote s Army were nodding, some enthusiastically, others solemnly. A couple of them rose from their chairs to demonstrate their willingness for immediate action.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You don\rquote t understand.\rdblquote  Harry seemed to have said that a lot in the last few hours. \ldblquote We \emdash  we can\rquote t tell you. We\rquote ve got to do it \emdash  alone.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Why?\rdblquote  asked Neville.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Because \'85\rdblquote  In his desperation to start looking for the miss\-ing Horcrux, or at least to have a private discussion with Ron and Hermione about where they might commence their search, Harry found it difficult to gather his thoughts. His scar was still searing. \ldblquote Dumbledore left the three of us a job,\rdblquote  he said carefully, \ldblquote and we weren\rquote t supposed to tell \emdash  I mean, he wanted us to do it, just the three of us.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote re his army,\rdblquote  said Neville. \ldblquote Dumbledore\rquote s Army. We were all in it together, we\rquote ve been keeping it going while you three have been off on your own \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It hasn\rquote t exactly been a picnic, mate,\rdblquote  said Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I never said it had, but I don\rquote t see why you can\rquote t trust us. Every\-one in this room\rquote s been fighting and they\rquote ve been driven in here because the Carrows were hunting them down. Everyone in here\rquote s proven they\rquote re loyal to Dumbledore \emdash  loyal to you.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Look,\rdblquote  Harry began, without knowing what he was going to say, but it did not matter: The tunnel door had just opened behind him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We got your message, Neville! Hello you three, I thought you must be here!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It was Luna and Dean. Seamus gave a great roar of delight and ran to hug his best friend.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hi, everyone!\rdblquote  said Luna happily. \ldblquote Oh, it\rquote s great to be back!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Luna,\rdblquote  said Harry distractedly, \ldblquote what are you doing here? How did you \emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I sent for her,\rdblquote  said Neville, holding up the fake Galleon. \ldblquote I promised her and Ginny that if you turned up I\rquote d let them know. We all thought that if you came back, it would mean revolution. That we were going to overthrow Snape and the Carrows.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Of course that\rquote s what it means,\rdblquote  said Luna brightly. \ldblquote Isn\rquote t it, Harry? We\rquote re going to fight them out of Hogwarts?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Listen,\rdblquote  said Harry with a rising sense of panic, \ldblquote I\rquote m sorry, but that\rquote s not what we came back for. There\rquote s something we\rquote ve got to do, and then \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re going to leave us in this mess?\rdblquote  demanded Michael Corner.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No!\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote What we\rquote re doing will benefit everyone in the end, it\rquote s all about trying to get rid of You-Know-Who \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Then let us help!\rdblquote  said Neville angrily. \ldblquote We want to be a part of it!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was another noise behind them, and Harry turned. His heart seemed to fail: Ginny was now climbing through the hole in the wall, closely followed by Fred, George, and Lee Jordan. Ginny gave Harry a radiant smile: He had forgotten, or had never fully ap\-preciated, how beautiful she was, but he had never been less pleased to see her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Aberforth\rquote s getting a bit annoyed,\rdblquote  said Fred, raising his hand in answer to several cries of greeting. \ldblquote He wants a kip, and his bar\rquote s turned into a railway station.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s mouth fell open. Right behind Lee Jordan came Harry\rquote s old girlfriend, Cho Chang. She smiled at him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I got the message,\rdblquote  she said, holding up her own fake Galleon, and she walked over to sit beside Michael Corner.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So what\rquote s the plan, Harry?\rdblquote  said George.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There isn\rquote t one,\rdblquote  said Harry, still disoriented by the sudden ap\-pearance of all these people, unable to take everything in while his scar was still burning so fiercely.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Just going to make it up as we go along, are we? My favorite kind,\rdblquote  said Fred.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote ve got to stop this!\rdblquote  Harry told Neville. \ldblquote What did you call them all back for? This is insane \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote re fighting, aren\rquote t we?\rdblquote  said Dean, taking out his fake Gal\-leon. \ldblquote The message said Harry was back, and we were going to fight! I\rquote ll have to get a wand, though \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You haven\rquote t got a \i wand\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\emdash  ?\rdblquote  began Seamus.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron turned suddenly to Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Why can\rquote t they help?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote They can help.\rdblquote  He dropped his voice and said, so that none of them could hear but Hermione, who stood between them, \ldblquote We don\rquote t know where it is. We\rquote ve got to find it fast. We don\rquote t have to tell them it\rquote s a Horcrux.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry looked from Ron to Hermione, who murmured, \ldblquote I think Ron\rquote s right. We don\rquote t even know what we\rquote re looking for, we need them.\rdblquote  And when Harry looked unconvinced, \ldblquote You don\rquote t have to do everything alone, Harry.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry thought fast, his scar still prickling, his head threatening to split again. Dumbledore had warned him against telling anyone but Ron and Hermione about the Horcruxes. \i Secrets and lies, that\rquote s how we grew up, and\lang3081  \lang1033 Albus\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\'85 \i he was a natural. \'85\i0  Was he turning into Dumbledore, keeping his secrets clutched to his chest, afraid to trust? But Dumbledore had trusted Snape, and where had that led? To murder at the top of the highest tower \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote All right,\rdblquote  he said quietly to the other two. \ldblquote Okay,\rdblquote  he called to the room at large, and all noise ceased: Fred and George, who had been cracking jokes for the benefit of those nearest, fell silent, and all of them looked alert, excited.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There\rquote s something we need to find,\rdblquote  Harry said. \ldblquote Some\-thing \emdash  something that\rquote ll help us overthrow You-Know-Who. It\rquote s here at Hogwarts, but we don\rquote t know where. It might have be\-longed to Ravenclaw. Has anyone heard of an object like that? Has anyone ever come across something with her eagle on it, for instance?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He looked hopefully toward the little group of Ravenclaws, to\lang3081  \lang1033 Padma, Michael, Terry, and Cho, but it was Luna who answered, perched on the arm of Ginny\rquote s chair.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, there\rquote s her lost diadem. I told you about it, remember, Harry? The lost diadem of Ravenclaw? Daddy\rquote s trying to dupli\-cate it.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, but the lost diadem,\rdblquote  said Michael Corner, rolling his eyes, \ldblquote is \i lost,\i0  Luna. That\rquote s sort of the point.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote When was it lost?\rdblquote  asked Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Centuries ago, they say,\rdblquote  said Cho, and Harry\rquote s heart sank. \ldblquote Pro\-fessor Flitwick says the diadem vanished with Ravenclaw herself. People have looked, but,\rdblquote  she appealed to her fellow Ravenclaws, \ldblquote nobody\rquote s ever found a trace of it, have they?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They all shook their heads.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Sorry, but what \i is\i0  a diadem?\rdblquote  asked Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s a kind of crown,\rdblquote  said Terry Boot. \ldblquote Ravenclaw\rquote s was supposed to have magical properties, enhance the wisdom of the wearer.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes, Daddy\rquote s Wrackspurt siphons \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Harry cut across Luna.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And none of you have ever seen anything that looks like it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They all shook their heads again. Harry looked at Ron and Her\-mione and his own disappointment was mirrored back at him. An object that had been lost this long, and apparently without trace, did not seem like a good candidate for the Horcrux hidden in the castle. \'85 Before he could formulate a new question, however, Cho spoke again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote If you\rquote d like to see what the diadem\rquote s supposed to look like, I could take you up to our common room and show you, Harry? Ravenclaw\rquote s wearing it in her statue.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s scar scorched again: For a moment the Room of Require\-ment swam before him, and he saw instead the dark earth soaring beneath him and felt the great snake wrapped around his shoulders. Voldemort was flying again, whether to the underground lake or here, to the castle, he did not know: Either way, there was hardly any time left.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He\rquote s on the move,\rdblquote  he said quietly to Ron and Hermione. He glanced at Cho and then back at them. \ldblquote Listen, I know it\rquote s not much of a lead, but I\rquote m going to go and look at this statue, at least find out what the diadem looks like. Wait for me here and keep, you know \emdash  the other one \emdash  safe.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Cho had got to her feet, but Ginny said rather fiercely, \ldblquote No, Luna will take Harry, won\rquote t you, Luna?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oooh, yes, I\rquote d like to,\rdblquote  said Luna happily, and Cho sat down again, looking disappointed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How do we get out?\rdblquote  Harry asked Neville.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Over here.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He led Harry and Luna to a corner, where a small cupboard opened onto a steep staircase.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It comes out somewhere different every day, so they\rquote ve never been able to find it,\rdblquote  he said. \ldblquote Only trouble is, we never know exactly where we\rquote re going to end up when we go out. Be careful, Harry, they\rquote re always patrolling the corridors at night.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No problem,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote See you in a bit.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He and Luna hurried up the staircase, which was long, lit by torches, and turned corners in unexpected places. At last they reached what appeared to be solid wall.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Get under here,\rdblquote  Harry told Luna, pulling out the Invisibility Cloak and throwing it over both of them. He gave the wall a little push.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It melted away at his touch and they slipped outside: Harry glanced back and saw that it had resealed itself at once. They were stand\-ing in a dark corridor: Harry pulled Luna back into the shadows, fumbled in the pouch around his neck, and took out the Marauder\rquote s Map. Holding it close to his nose he searched, and located his and Luna\rquote s dots at last.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote re up on the fifth floor,\rdblquote  he whispered, watching Filch mov\-ing away from them, a corridor ahead. \ldblquote Come on, this way.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They crept off.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry had prowled the castle at night many times before, but never had his heart hammered this fast, never had so much de\-pended on his safe passage through the place. Through squares of moonlight upon the floor, past suits of armor whose helmets creaked at the sound of their soft footsteps, around corners beyond which who knew what lurked, Harry and Luna walked, checking the Marauder\rquote s Map whenever light permitted, twice pausing to allow a ghost to pass without drawing attention to themselves. He expected to encounter an obstacle at any moment; his worst fear was Peeves, and he strained his ears with every step to hear the first, telltale signs of the poltergeist\rquote s approach.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote This way, Harry,\rdblquote  breathed Luna, plucking his sleeve and pulling him toward a spiral staircase.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They climbed in tight, dizzying circles; Harry had never been up here before. At last they reached a door. There was no handle and no keyhole: nothing but a plain expanse of aged wood, and a bronze knocker in the shape of an eagle.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Luna reached out a pale hand, which looked eerie floating in midair, unconnected to arm or body. She knocked once, and in the silence it sounded to Harry like a cannon blast. At once the beak of\lang3081  \lang1033 the eagle opened, but instead of a bird\rquote s call, a soft, musical voice said, \ldblquote Which came first, the phoenix or the flame?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hmm \'85 What do you think, Harry?\rdblquote  said Luna, looking thoughtful.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What? Isn\rquote t there just a password?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh no, you\rquote ve got to answer a question,\rdblquote  said Luna.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What if you get it wrong?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, you have to wait for somebody who gets it right,\rdblquote  said Luna. \ldblquote That way you learn, you see?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah \'85 Trouble is, we can\rquote t really afford to wait for anyone else, Luna.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, I see what you mean,\rdblquote  said Luna seriously. \ldblquote Well then, I think the answer is that a circle has no beginning.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well reasoned,\rdblquote  said the voice, and the door swung open.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The deserted Ravenclaw common room was a wide, circular room, airier than any Harry had ever seen at Hogwarts. Graceful arched windows punctuated the walls, which were hung with blue-and-bronze silks: By day, the Ravenclaws would have a spectacular view of the surrounding mountains. The ceiling was domed and painted with stars, which were echoed in the midnight-blue carpet. There were tables, chairs, and bookcases, and in a niche opposite the door stood a tall statue of white marble.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry recognized Rowena Ravenclaw from the bust he had seen at Luna\rquote s house. The statue stood beside a door that led, he guessed, to dormitories above. He strode right up to the marble woman, and she seemed to look back at him with a quizzical half smile on her face, beautiful yet slightly intimidating. A delicate-looking circlet had been reproduced in marble on top of her head. It was not un\-like the tiara Fleur had worn at her wedding. There were tiny words\lang3081  \lang1033 etched into it. Harry stepped out from under the Cloak and climbed up onto Ravenclaw\rquote s plinth to read them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \lquote\i Wit beyond measure is man\rquote s greatest treasure.\i0\rquote  \rdblquote\i\par
\i0\ldblquote Which makes you pretty skint, witless,\rdblquote  said a cackling voice.\par
Harry whirled around, slipped off the plinth, and landed on the floor. The sloping-shouldered figure of Alecto Carrow was standing before him, and even as Harry raised his wand, she pressed a stubby forefinger to the skull and snake branded on her forearm.\lang3081\par
