The moment her finger touched the Mark, Harry\rquote s scar burned savagely, the starry room vanished from sight, and he was standing upon an outcrop of rock beneath a cliff, and the sea was washing around him and there was triumph in his heart \emdash  \i They have the boy.\i0\par
A loud \i bang\i0  brought Harry back to where he stood: Disoriented, he raised his wand, but the witch before him was already falling forward; she hit the ground so hard that the glass in the bookcases tinkled.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ve never Stunned anyone except in our D.A. lessons,\rdblquote  said Luna, sounding mildly interested. \ldblquote That was noisier than I thought it would be.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
