He was lying facedown on the ground again. The smell of the forest filled his nostrils. He could feel the cold hard ground beneath his cheek, and the hinge of his glasses, which had been knocked sideways by the fall, cutting into his temple. Every inch of him ached, and the place where the Killing Curse had hit him felt like the bruise of an iron-clad punch. He did not stir, but remained exactly where he had fallen, with his left arm bent out at an awkward angle and his mouth gaping.\par
He had expected to hear cheers of triumph and jubilation at his death, but instead hurried footsteps, whispers, and solicitous mur\-murs filled the air.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote My Lord \'85 \i my Lord\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It was Bellatrix\rquote s voice, and she spoke as if to a lover. Harry did not dare open his eyes, but allowed his other senses to explore his predicament. He knew that his wand was still stowed beneath his robes because he could feel it pressed between his chest and the\lang3081  \lang1033 ground. A slight cushioning effect in the area of his stomach told him that the Invisibility Cloak was also there, stuffed out of sight.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i My Lord\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That will do,\rdblquote  said Voldemort\rquote s voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 More footsteps: Several people were backing away from the same spot. Desperate to see what was happening and why, Harry opened his eyes by a millimeter.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Voldemort seemed to be getting to his feet. Various Death Eat\-ers were hurrying away from him, returning to the crowd lining the clearing. Bellatrix alone remained behind, kneeling beside Voldemort.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry closed his eyes again and considered what he had seen. The Death Eaters had been huddled around Voldemort, who seemed to have fallen to the ground. Something had happened when he had hit Harry with the Killing Curse. Had Voldemort too collapsed? It seemed like it. And both of them had fallen briefly unconscious and both of them had now returned. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote My Lord, let me \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I do not require assistance,\rdblquote  said Voldemort coldly, and though he could not see it, Harry pictured Bellatrix withdrawing a helpful hand. \ldblquote The boy \'85 Is he dead?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was complete silence in the clearing. Nobody approached Harry, but he felt their concentrated gaze; it seemed to press him harder into the ground, and he was terrified a finger or an eyelid might twitch.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You,\rdblquote  said Voldemort, and there was a bang and a small shriek of pain. \ldblquote Examine him. Tell me whether he is dead.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry did not know who had been sent to verify. He could only lie there, with his heart thumping traitorously, and wait to be\lang3081  \lang1033 examined, but at the same time noting, small comfort though it was, that Voldemort was wary of approaching him, that Voldemort suspected that all had not gone to plan. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hands, softer than he had been expecting, touched Harry\rquote s face, pulled back an eyelid, crept beneath his shirt, down to his chest, and felt his heart. He could hear the woman\rquote s fast breathing, her long hair tickled his face. He knew that she could feel the steady pounding of life against his ribs.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Is Draco alive\i0 ? \i Is he in the castle\i0 ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The whisper was barely audible; her lips were an inch from his ear, her head bent so low that her long hair shielded his face from the onlookers.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Yes,\i0\rdblquote  he breathed back.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He felt the hand on his chest contract; her nails pierced him. Then it was withdrawn. She had sat up.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He is dead!\rdblquote  Narcissa Malfoy called to the watchers.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And now they shouted, now they yelled in triumph and stamped their feet, and through his eyelids, Harry saw bursts of red and silver light shoot into the air in celebration.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Still feigning death on the ground, he understood. Narcissa knew that the only way she would be permitted to enter Hogwarts, and find her son, was as part of the conquering army. She no longer cared whether Voldemort won.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You see?\rdblquote  screeched Voldemort over the tumult. \ldblquote Harry Potter is dead by my hand, and no man alive can threaten me now! Watch! \i Crucio\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry had been expecting it, knew his body would not be allowed to remain unsullied upon the forest floor; it must be subjected to humiliation to prove Voldemort\rquote s victory. He was lifted into the\lang3081  \lang1033 air, and it took all his determination to remain limp, yet the pain he expected did not come. He was thrown once, twice, three times into the air: His glasses flew off and he felt his wand slide a little beneath his robes, but he kept himself floppy and lifeless, and when he fell to the ground for the last time, the clearing echoed with jeers and shrieks of laughter.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Now,\rdblquote  said Voldemort, \ldblquote we go to the castle, and show them what has become of their hero. Who shall drag the body? No \emdash\lang3081  \lang1033 Wait\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a fresh outbreak of laughter, and after a few moments Harry felt the ground trembling beneath him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You carry him,\rdblquote  Voldemort said. \ldblquote He will be nice and visible in your arms, will he not? Pick up your little friend, Hagrid. And the glasses \emdash  put on the glasses \emdash  he must be recognizable \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Someone slammed Harry\rquote s glasses back onto his face with deliber\-ate force, but the enormous hands that lifted him into the air were exceedingly gentle. Harry could feel Hagrid\rquote s arms trembling with the force of his heaving sobs; great tears splashed down upon him as Hagrid cradled Harry in his arms, and Harry did not dare, by move\-ment or word, to intimate to Hagrid that all was not, yet, lost.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Move,\rdblquote  said Voldemort, and Hagrid stumbled forward, forcing his way through the close-growing trees, back through the forest. Branches caught at Harry\rquote s hair and robes, but he lay quiescent, his mouth lolling open, his eyes shut, and in the darkness, while the Death Eaters crowed all around them, and while Hagrid sobbed blindly, nobody looked to see whether a pulse beat in the exposed neck of Harry Potter. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The two giants crashed along behind the Death Eaters; Harry could hear trees creaking and falling as they passed; they made so\lang3081  \lang1033 much din that birds rose shrieking into the sky, and even the jeers of the Death Eaters were drowned. The victorious procession marched on toward the open ground, and after a while Harry could tell, by the lightening of the darkness through his closed eyelids, that the trees were beginning to thin.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote BANE!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hagrid\rquote s unexpected bellow nearly forced Harry\rquote s eyes open. \ldblquote Happy now, are yeh, that yeh didn\rquote  fight, yeh cowardly bunch o\rquote  nags? Are yeh happy Harry Potter\rquote s \emdash  d-dead \'85 ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hagrid could not continue, but broke down in fresh tears. Harry wondered how many centaurs were watching their procession pass; he dared not open his eyes to look. Some of the Death Eaters called insults at the centaurs as they left them behind. A little later, Harry sensed, by a freshening of the air, that they had reached the edge of the forest.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Stop.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry thought that Hagrid must have been forced to obey Volde\-mort\rquote s command, because he lurched a little. And now a chill settled over them where they stood, and Harry heard the rasping breath of the dementors that patrolled the outer trees. They would not affect him now. The fact of his own survival burned inside him, a talisman against them, as though his father\rquote s stag kept guardian in his heart.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Someone passed close by Harry, and he knew that it was Volde\-mort himself because he spoke a moment later, his voice magically magnified so that it swelled through the grounds, crashing upon Harry\rquote s eardrums.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry Potter is dead. He was killed as he ran away, trying to save himself while you lay down your lives for him. We bring you his body as proof that your hero is gone.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The battle is won. You have lost half of your fighters. My Death Eaters outnumber you, and the Boy Who Lived is finished. There must be no more war. Anyone who continues to resist, man, woman, or child, will be slaughtered, as will every member of their fam\-ily. Come out of the castle now, kneel before me, and you shall be spared. Your parents and children, your brothers and sisters will live and be forgiven, and you will join me in the new world we shall build together.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was silence in the grounds and from the castle. Voldemort was so close to him that Harry did not dare open his eyes again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Come,\rdblquote  said Voldemort, and Harry heard him move ahead, and Hagrid was forced to follow. Now Harry opened his eyes a fraction, and saw Voldemort striding in front of them, wearing the great snake Nagini around his shoulders, now free of her enchanted cage. But Harry had no possibility of extracting the wand concealed under his robes without being noticed by the Death Eaters, who marched on either side of them through the slowly lightening darkness. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry,\rdblquote  sobbed Hagrid. \ldblquote Oh, Harry \'85 Harry \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry shut his eyes tight again. He knew that they were ap\-proaching the castle and strained his ears to distinguish, above the gleeful voices of the Death Eaters and their tramping footsteps, signs of life from those within.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Stop.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
