Autumn seemed to arrive suddenly that year. The morning of the first of September was crisp and golden as an apple, and as the little family bobbed across the rumbling road toward the great sooty station, the fumes of car exhausts and the breath of pedestrians sparkled like cobwebs in the cold air. Two large cages rattled on top of the laden trolleys the parents were pushing; the owls inside them hooted indignantly, and the redheaded girl trailed tearfully behind her brothers, clutching her father\rquote s arm.\par
\ldblquote It won\rquote t be long, and you\rquote ll be going too,\rdblquote  Harry told her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Two years,\rdblquote  sniffed Lily. \ldblquote I want to go \i now\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The commuters stared curiously at the owls as the family wove its way toward the barrier between platforms nine and ten. Albus\rquote s voice drifted back to Harry over the surrounding clamor; his sons had resumed the argument they had started in the car.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I \i won\rquote t\i0 ! I \i won\rquote t\i0  be in Slytherin!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote James, give it a rest!\rdblquote  said Ginny.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I only said he \i might\i0  be,\rdblquote  said James, grinning at his younger brother. \ldblquote There\rquote s nothing wrong with that. He \i might\i0  be in Slyth \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But James caught his mother\rquote s eye and fell silent. The five Potters approached the barrier. With a slightly cocky look over his shoulder at his younger brother, James took the trolley from his mother and broke into a run. A moment later, he had vanished.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote ll write to me, won\rquote t you?\rdblquote  Albus asked his parents immedi\-ately, capitalizing on the momentary absence of his brother.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Every day, if you want us to,\rdblquote  said Ginny.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Not \i every\i0  day,\rdblquote  said Albus quickly. \ldblquote James says most people only get letters from home about once a month.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We wrote to James three times a week last year,\rdblquote  said Ginny.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And you don\rquote t want to believe everything he tells you about Hogwarts,\rdblquote  Harry put in. \ldblquote He likes a laugh, your brother.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Side by side, they pushed the second trolley forward, gathering speed. As they reached the barrier, Albus winced, but no collision came. Instead, the family emerged onto platform nine and three-quarters, which was obscured by thick white steam that was pouring from the scarlet Hogwarts Express. Indistinct figures were swarming through the mist, into which James had already disappeared.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Where are they?\rdblquote  asked Albus anxiously, peering at the hazy forms they passed as they made their way down the platform.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote ll find them,\rdblquote  said Ginny reassuringly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But the vapor was dense, and it was difficult to make out any\-body\rquote s faces. Detached from their owners, voices sounded unnatu\-rally loud. Harry thought he heard Percy discoursing loudly on broomstick regulations, and was quite glad of the excuse not to stop and say hello. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I think that\rquote s them, Al,\rdblquote  said Ginny suddenly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A group of four people emerged from the mist, standing alongside the very last carriage. Their faces only came into focus when Harry, Ginny, Lily, and Albus had drawn right up to them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hi,\rdblquote  said Albus, sounding immensely relieved.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Rose, who was already wearing her brand-new Hogwarts robes, beamed at him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Parked all right, then?\rdblquote  Ron asked Harry. \ldblquote I did. Hermione didn\rquote t believe I could pass a Muggle driving test, did you? She thought I\rquote d have to Confund the examiner.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, I didn\rquote t,\rdblquote  said Hermione, \ldblquote I had complete faith in you.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote As a matter of fact, I \i did\i0  Confund him,\rdblquote  Ron whispered to Harry, as together they lifted Albus\rquote s trunk and owl onto the train. \ldblquote I only forgot to look in the wing mirror, and let\rquote s face it, I can use a Supersensory Charm for that.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Back on the platform, they found Lily and Hugo, Rose\rquote s younger brother, having an animated discussion about which House they would be sorted into when they finally went to Hogwarts.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote If you\rquote re not in Gryffindor, we\rquote ll disinherit you,\rdblquote  said Ron, \ldblquote but no pressure.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Ron\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lily and Hugo laughed, but Albus and Rose looked solemn.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He doesn\rquote t mean it,\rdblquote  said Hermione and Ginny, but Ron was no longer paying attention. Catching Harry\rquote s eye, he nodded covertly to a point some fifty yards away. The steam had thinned for a moment, and three people stood in sharp relief against the shifting mist.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Look who it is.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Draco Malfoy was standing there with his wife and son, a dark coat buttoned up to his throat. His hair was receding somewhat,\lang3081  \lang1033 which emphasized the pointed chin. The new boy resembled Draco as much as Albus resembled Harry. Draco caught sight of Harry, Ron, Hermione, and Ginny staring at him, nodded curtly, and turned away again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So that\rquote s little Scorpius,\rdblquote  said Ron under his breath. \ldblquote Make sure you beat him in every test, Rosie. Thank God you inherited your mother\rquote s brains.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ron, for heaven\rquote s sake,\rdblquote  said Hermione, half stern, half amused. \ldblquote Don\rquote t try to turn them against each other before they\rquote ve even started school!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re right, sorry,\rdblquote  said Ron, but unable to help himself, he added, \ldblquote Don\rquote t get \i too\i0  friendly with him, though, Rosie. Granddad Weasley would never forgive you if you married a pureblood.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hey!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 James had reappeared; he had divested himself of his trunk, owl, and trolley, and was evidently bursting with news.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Teddy\rquote s back there,\rdblquote  he said breathlessly, pointing back over his shoulder into the billowing clouds of steam. \ldblquote Just seen him! And guess what he\rquote s doing? \i Snogging Victoire\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He gazed up at the adults, evidently disappointed by the lack of reaction.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Our \i0 Teddy! \i Teddy Lupin\i0 ! Snogging \i our\i0  Victoire! \i Our\i0  cousin! And I asked Teddy what he was doing \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You interrupted them?\rdblquote  said Ginny. \ldblquote You are \i so\i0  like Ron \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\emdash  and he said he\rquote d come to see her off! And then he told me to go away. He\rquote s \i snogging\i0  her!\rdblquote  James added as though worried he had not made himself clear.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, it would be lovely if they got married!\rdblquote  whispered Lily ec\-statically. \ldblquote Teddy would \i really\i0  be part of the family then!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He already comes round for dinner about four times a week,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote Why don\rquote t we just invite him to live with us and have done with it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah!\rdblquote  said James enthusiastically. \ldblquote I don\rquote t mind sharing with Al \emdash  Teddy could have my room!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said Harry firmly, \ldblquote you and Al will share a room only when I want the house demolished.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He checked the battered old watch that had once been Fabian Prewett\rquote s.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s nearly eleven, you\rquote d better get on board.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t forget to give Neville our love!\rdblquote  Ginny told James as she hugged him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Mum! I can\rquote t give a professor \i love\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But you \i know\i0  Neville \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 James rolled his eyes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Outside, yeah, but at school he\rquote s Professor Longbottom, isn\rquote t he? I can\rquote t walk into Herbology and give him \i love. \'85\i0\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Shaking his head at his mother\rquote s foolishness, he vented his feel\-ings by aiming a kick at Albus.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote See you later, Al. Watch out for the thestrals.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I thought they were invisible? \i You said they were invisible\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But James merely laughed, permitted his mother to kiss him, gave his father a fleeting hug, then leapt onto the rapidly filling train. They saw him wave, then sprint away up the corridor to find his friends.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Thestrals are nothing to worry about,\rdblquote  Harry told Albus. \ldblquote They\rquote re gentle things, there\rquote s nothing scary about them. Anyway, you won\rquote t be going up to school in the carriages, you\rquote ll be going in the boats.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ginny kissed Albus good-bye.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote See you at Christmas.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Bye, Al,\rdblquote  said Harry as his son hugged him. \ldblquote Don\rquote t forget Hagrid\rquote s invited you to tea next Friday. Don\rquote t mess with Peeves. Don\rquote t duel anyone till you\rquote ve learned how. And don\rquote t let James wind you up.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What if I\rquote m in Slytherin?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The whisper was for his father alone, and Harry knew that only the moment of departure could have forced Albus to reveal how great and sincere that fear was.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry crouched down so that Albus\rquote s face was slightly above his own. Alone of Harry\rquote s three children, Albus had inherited Lily\rquote s eyes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Albus Severus,\rdblquote  Harry said quietly, so that nobody but Ginny could hear, and she was tactful enough to pretend to be waving to Rose, who was now on the train, \ldblquote you were named for two headmas\-ters of Hogwarts. One of them was a Slytherin and he was probably the bravest man I ever knew.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i But just say\i0  \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\emdash  then Slytherin House will have gained an excellent student, won\rquote t it? It doesn\rquote t matter to us, Al. But if it matters to you, you\rquote ll be able to choose Gryffindor over Slytherin. The Sorting Hat takes your choice into account.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Really?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It did for me,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He had never told any of his children that before, and he saw the wonder in Albus\rquote s face when he said it. But now the doors were slamming all along the scarlet train, and the blurred outlines of par\-ents were swarming forward for final kisses, last-minute reminders.\lang3081  \lang1033 Albus jumped into the carriage and Ginny closed the door behind him. Students were hanging from the windows nearest them. A great number of faces, both on the train and off, seemed to be turned toward Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Why are they all \i staring\i0 ?\rdblquote  demanded Albus as he and Rose craned around to look at the other students.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t let it worry you,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote It\rquote s me. I\rquote m extremely famous.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Albus, Rose, Hugo, and Lily laughed. The train began to move, and Harry walked alongside it, watching his son\rquote s thin face, al\-ready ablaze with excitement. Harry kept smiling and waving, even though it was like a little bereavement, watching his son glide away from him. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The last trace of steam evaporated in the autumn air. The train rounded a corner. Harry\rquote s hand was still raised in farewell.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He\rquote ll be all right,\rdblquote  murmured Ginny.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 As Harry looked at her, he lowered his hand absentmindedly and touched the lightning scar on his forehead.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I know he will.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The scar had not pained Harry for nineteen years. All was well.\lang3081\par
